83 constexpr bool IsOSR(BytecodeOffset osr_offset) { return !osr_offset.IsNone(); }
84 
85 class CompilerTracer : public AllStatic {
86  public:
87  static void TraceStartBaselineCompile(
88  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared) {
89  if (!v8_flags.trace_baseline) return;
90  CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
91  PrintTracePrefix(scope, "compiling method", shared, CodeKind::BASELINE);
92  PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
93  }
94 
95  static void TraceStartMaglevCompile(Isolate* isolate,
96  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
97  bool osr, ConcurrencyMode mode) {
98  if (!v8_flags.trace_opt) return;
99  CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
100  PrintTracePrefix(scope, "compiling method", function, CodeKind::MAGLEV);
101  if (osr) PrintF(scope.file(), " OSR");
102  PrintF(scope.file(), ", mode: %s", ToString(mode));
103  PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
104  }
105 
106  static void TracePrepareJob(Isolate* isolate, OptimizedCompilationInfo* info,
107  ConcurrencyMode mode) {
108  if (!v8_flags.trace_opt || !info->IsOptimizing()) return;
109  CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
110  PrintTracePrefix(scope, "compiling method", info);
111  if (info->is_osr()) PrintF(scope.file(), " OSR");
112  PrintF(scope.file(), ", mode: %s", ToString(mode));
113  PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
114  }
115 
116  static void TraceOptimizeOSRStarted(Isolate* isolate,
117  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
118  BytecodeOffset osr_offset,
119  ConcurrencyMode mode) {
120  if (!v8_flags.trace_osr) return;
121  CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
122  PrintF(
123  scope.file(),
124  "[OSR - compilation started. function: %s, osr offset: %d, mode: %s]\n",
125  function->DebugNameCStr().get(), osr_offset.ToInt(), ToString(mode));
126  }
127 
128  static void TraceOptimizeOSRFinished(Isolate* isolate,
129  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
130  BytecodeOffset osr_offset) {
131  if (!v8_flags.trace_osr) return;
132  CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
133  PrintF(scope.file(),
134  "[OSR - compilation finished. function: %s, osr offset: %d]\n",
135  function->DebugNameCStr().get(), osr_offset.ToInt());
136  }
137 
138  static void TraceOptimizeOSRAvailable(Isolate* isolate,
139  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
140  BytecodeOffset osr_offset,
141  ConcurrencyMode mode) {
142  if (!v8_flags.trace_osr) return;
143  CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
144  PrintF(scope.file(),
145  "[OSR - available (compilation completed or cache hit). function: "
146  "%s, osr offset: %d, mode: %s]\n",
147  function->DebugNameCStr().get(), osr_offset.ToInt(), ToString(mode));
148  }
149 
150  static void TraceOptimizeOSRUnavailable(Isolate* isolate,
151  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
152  BytecodeOffset osr_offset,
153  ConcurrencyMode mode) {
154  if (!v8_flags.trace_osr) return;
155  CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
156  PrintF(scope.file(),
157  "[OSR - unavailable (failed or in progress). function: %s, osr "
158  "offset: %d, mode: %s]\n",
159  function->DebugNameCStr().get(), osr_offset.ToInt(), ToString(mode));
160  }
161 
162  static void TraceFinishTurbofanCompile(Isolate* isolate,
163  OptimizedCompilationInfo* info,
164  double ms_creategraph,
165  double ms_optimize,
166  double ms_codegen) {
167  DCHECK(v8_flags.trace_opt);
168  DCHECK(info->IsOptimizing());
169  CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
170  PrintTracePrefix(scope, "completed compiling", info);
171  if (info->is_osr()) PrintF(scope.file(), " OSR");
172  PrintF(scope.file(), " - took %0.3f, %0.3f, %0.3f ms", ms_creategraph,
173  ms_optimize, ms_codegen);
174  PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
175  }
176 
177  static void TraceFinishBaselineCompile(
178  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
179  double ms_timetaken) {
180  if (!v8_flags.trace_baseline) return;
181  CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
182  PrintTracePrefix(scope, "completed compiling", shared, CodeKind::BASELINE);
183  PrintF(scope.file(), " - took %0.3f ms", ms_timetaken);
184  PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
185  }
186 
187  static void TraceFinishMaglevCompile(Isolate* isolate,
188  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
189  bool osr, double ms_prepare,
190  double ms_execute, double ms_finalize) {
191  if (!v8_flags.trace_opt) return;
192  CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
193  PrintTracePrefix(scope, "completed compiling", function, CodeKind::MAGLEV);
194  if (osr) PrintF(scope.file(), " OSR");
195  PrintF(scope.file(), " - took %0.3f, %0.3f, %0.3f ms", ms_prepare,
196  ms_execute, ms_finalize);
197  PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
198  }
199 
200  static void TraceAbortedMaglevCompile(Isolate* isolate,
201  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
202  BailoutReason bailout_reason) {
203  if (!v8_flags.trace_opt) return;
204  CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
205  PrintTracePrefix(scope, "aborted compiling", function, CodeKind::MAGLEV);
206  PrintF(scope.file(), " because: %s", GetBailoutReason(bailout_reason));
207  PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
208  }
209 
210  static void TraceCompletedJob(Isolate* isolate,
211  OptimizedCompilationInfo* info) {
212  if (!v8_flags.trace_opt) return;
213  CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
214  PrintTracePrefix(scope, "completed optimizing", info);
215  if (info->is_osr()) PrintF(scope.file(), " OSR");
216  PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
217  }
218 
219  static void TraceAbortedJob(Isolate* isolate, OptimizedCompilationInfo* info,
220  double ms_prepare, double ms_execute,
221  double ms_finalize) {
222  if (!v8_flags.trace_opt) return;
223  CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
224  PrintTracePrefix(scope, "aborted optimizing", info);
225  if (info->is_osr()) PrintF(scope.file(), " OSR");
226  PrintF(scope.file(), " because: %s",
227  GetBailoutReason(info->bailout_reason()));
228  PrintF(scope.file(), " - took %0.3f, %0.3f, %0.3f ms", ms_prepare,
229  ms_execute, ms_finalize);
230  PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
231  }
232 
233  static void TraceOptimizedCodeCacheHit(Isolate* isolate,
234  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
235  BytecodeOffset osr_offset,
236  CodeKind code_kind) {
237  if (!v8_flags.trace_opt) return;
238  CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
239  PrintTracePrefix(scope, "found optimized code for", function, code_kind);
240  if (IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
241  PrintF(scope.file(), " at OSR bytecode offset %d", osr_offset.ToInt());
242  }
243  PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
244  }
245 
246  static void TraceOptimizeForAlwaysOpt(Isolate* isolate,
247  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
248  CodeKind code_kind) {
249  if (!v8_flags.trace_opt) return;
250  CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
251  PrintTracePrefix(scope, "optimizing", function, code_kind);
252  PrintF(scope.file(), " because --always-turbofan");
253  PrintTraceSuffix(scope);
254  }
255 
256  static void TraceMarkForAlwaysOpt(Isolate* isolate,
257  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function) {
258  if (!v8_flags.trace_opt) return;
259  CodeTracer::Scope scope(isolate->GetCodeTracer());
260  PrintF(scope.file(), "[marking ");
261  ShortPrint(*function, scope.file());
262  PrintF(scope.file(),
263  " for optimized recompilation because --always-turbofan");
264  PrintF(scope.file(), "]\n");
265  }
266 
267  private:
268  static void PrintTracePrefix(const CodeTracer::Scope& scope,
269  const char* header,
270  OptimizedCompilationInfo* info) {
271  PrintTracePrefix(scope, header, info->closure(), info->code_kind());
272  }
273 
274  static void PrintTracePrefix(const CodeTracer::Scope& scope,
275  const char* header,
276  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
277  CodeKind code_kind) {
278  PrintF(scope.file(), "[%s ", header);
279  ShortPrint(*function, scope.file());
280  PrintF(scope.file(), " (target %s)", CodeKindToString(code_kind));
281  }
282 
283  static void PrintTracePrefix(const CodeTracer::Scope& scope,
284  const char* header,
285  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
286  CodeKind code_kind) {
287  PrintF(scope.file(), "[%s ", header);
288  ShortPrint(*shared, scope.file());
289  PrintF(scope.file(), " (target %s)", CodeKindToString(code_kind));
290  }
291 
292  static void PrintTraceSuffix(const CodeTracer::Scope& scope) {
293  PrintF(scope.file(), "]\n");
294  }
295 };
296 
297 } // namespace
298 
299 // static
300 void Compiler::LogFunctionCompilation(Isolate* isolate,
301  LogEventListener::CodeTag code_type,
302  DirectHandle<Script> script,
303  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
304  DirectHandle<FeedbackVector> vector,
305  DirectHandle<AbstractCode> abstract_code,
306  CodeKind kind, double time_taken_ms) {
307  DCHECK_NE(*abstract_code,
308  Cast<AbstractCode>(*BUILTIN_CODE(isolate, CompileLazy)));
309 
310  // Log the code generation. If source information is available include
311  // script name and line number. Check explicitly whether logging is
312  // enabled as finding the line number is not free.
313  if (!isolate->IsLoggingCodeCreation()) return;
314 
315  Script::PositionInfo info;
316  Script::GetPositionInfo(script, shared->StartPosition(), &info);
317  int line_num = info.line + 1;
318  int column_num = info.column + 1;
319  DirectHandle<String> script_name(IsString(script->name())
320  ? Cast<String>(script->name())
321  : ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_string(),
322  isolate);
323  LogEventListener::CodeTag log_tag =
324  V8FileLogger::ToNativeByScript(code_type, *script);
325  PROFILE(isolate, CodeCreateEvent(log_tag, abstract_code, shared, script_name,
326  line_num, column_num));
327  if (!vector.is_null()) {
328  LOG(isolate, FeedbackVectorEvent(*vector, *abstract_code));
329  }
330  if (!v8_flags.log_function_events) return;
331 
332  std::string name;
333  switch (kind) {
334  case CodeKind::INTERPRETED_FUNCTION:
335  name = "interpreter";
336  break;
337  case CodeKind::BASELINE:
338  name = "baseline";
339  break;
340  case CodeKind::MAGLEV:
341  name = "maglev";
342  break;
343  case CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS:
344  name = "turbofan";
345  break;
346  default:
347  UNREACHABLE();
348  }
349  switch (code_type) {
350  case LogEventListener::CodeTag::kEval:
351  name += "-eval";
352  break;
353  case LogEventListener::CodeTag::kScript:
354  case LogEventListener::CodeTag::kFunction:
355  break;
356  default:
357  UNREACHABLE();
358  }
359 
360  DirectHandle<String> debug_name =
361  SharedFunctionInfo::DebugName(isolate, shared);
362  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
363  LOG(isolate, FunctionEvent(name.c_str(), script->id(), time_taken_ms,
364  shared->StartPosition(), shared->EndPosition(),
365  *debug_name));
366 }
367 
368 namespace {
369 
370 ScriptOriginOptions OriginOptionsForEval(
371  Tagged<Object> script, ParsingWhileDebugging parsing_while_debugging) {
372  bool is_shared_cross_origin =
373  parsing_while_debugging == ParsingWhileDebugging::kYes;
374  bool is_opaque = false;
375  if (IsScript(script)) {
376  auto script_origin_options = Cast<Script>(script)->origin_options();
377  if (script_origin_options.IsSharedCrossOrigin()) {
378  is_shared_cross_origin = true;
379  }
380  if (script_origin_options.IsOpaque()) {
381  is_opaque = true;
382  }
383  }
384  return ScriptOriginOptions(is_shared_cross_origin, is_opaque);
385 }

390 // Implementation of UnoptimizedCompilationJob
391 
392 CompilationJob::Status UnoptimizedCompilationJob::ExecuteJob() {
393  // Delegate to the underlying implementation.
394  DCHECK_EQ(state(), State::kReadyToExecute);
395  base::ScopedTimer t(v8_flags.log_function_events ? &time_taken_to_execute_
396  : nullptr);
397  return UpdateState(ExecuteJobImpl(), State::kReadyToFinalize);
398 }
399 
400 CompilationJob::Status UnoptimizedCompilationJob::FinalizeJob(
401  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info, Isolate* isolate) {
402  DCHECK_EQ(ThreadId::Current(), isolate->thread_id());
403  DisallowCodeDependencyChange no_dependency_change;
404  DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
405 
406  // Delegate to the underlying implementation.
407  DCHECK_EQ(state(), State::kReadyToFinalize);
408  base::ScopedTimer t(v8_flags.log_function_events ? &time_taken_to_finalize_
409  : nullptr);
410  return UpdateState(FinalizeJobImpl(shared_info, isolate), State::kSucceeded);
411 }
412 
413 CompilationJob::Status UnoptimizedCompilationJob::FinalizeJob(
414  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info, LocalIsolate* isolate) {
415  // Delegate to the underlying implementation.
416  DCHECK_EQ(state(), State::kReadyToFinalize);
417  base::ScopedTimer t(v8_flags.log_function_events ? &time_taken_to_finalize_
418  : nullptr);
419  return UpdateState(FinalizeJobImpl(shared_info, isolate), State::kSucceeded);
420 }
421 
422 namespace {
423 void LogUnoptimizedCompilation(Isolate* isolate,
424  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
425  LogEventListener::CodeTag code_type,
426  base::TimeDelta time_taken_to_execute,
427  base::TimeDelta time_taken_to_finalize) {
428  DirectHandle<AbstractCode> abstract_code;
429  if (shared->HasBytecodeArray()) {
430  abstract_code = direct_handle(
431  Cast<AbstractCode>(shared->GetBytecodeArray(isolate)), isolate);
432  } else {
433 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
434  DCHECK(shared->HasAsmWasmData());
435  abstract_code = Cast<AbstractCode>(BUILTIN_CODE(isolate, InstantiateAsmJs));
436 #else
437  UNREACHABLE();
438 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
439  }
440 
441  double time_taken_ms = time_taken_to_execute.InMillisecondsF() +
442  time_taken_to_finalize.InMillisecondsF();
443 
444  DirectHandle<Script> script(Cast<Script>(shared->script()), isolate);
445  Compiler::LogFunctionCompilation(
446  isolate, code_type, script, shared, DirectHandle<FeedbackVector>(),
447  abstract_code, CodeKind::INTERPRETED_FUNCTION, time_taken_ms);
448 }

453 // Implementation of OptimizedCompilationJob
454 
455 CompilationJob::Status OptimizedCompilationJob::PrepareJob(Isolate* isolate) {
456  DCHECK_EQ(ThreadId::Current(), isolate->thread_id());
457  DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
458 
459  // Delegate to the underlying implementation.
460  DCHECK_EQ(state(), State::kReadyToPrepare);
461  base::ScopedTimer t(&time_taken_to_prepare_);
462  return UpdateState(PrepareJobImpl(isolate), State::kReadyToExecute);
463 }
464 
465 CompilationJob::Status OptimizedCompilationJob::ExecuteJob(
466  RuntimeCallStats* stats, LocalIsolate* local_isolate) {
467  DCHECK_IMPLIES(local_isolate && !local_isolate->is_main_thread(),
468  local_isolate->heap()->IsParked());
469  // Delegate to the underlying implementation.
470  DCHECK_EQ(state(), State::kReadyToExecute);
471  base::ScopedTimer t(&time_taken_to_execute_);
472  return UpdateState(ExecuteJobImpl(stats, local_isolate),
473  State::kReadyToFinalize);
474 }
475 
476 CompilationJob::Status OptimizedCompilationJob::FinalizeJob(Isolate* isolate) {
477  DCHECK_EQ(ThreadId::Current(), isolate->thread_id());
478  DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
479 
480  // Delegate to the underlying implementation.
481  DCHECK_EQ(state(), State::kReadyToFinalize);
482  base::ScopedTimer t(&time_taken_to_finalize_);
483  return UpdateState(FinalizeJobImpl(isolate), State::kSucceeded);
484 }
485 
486 GlobalHandleVector<Map> OptimizedCompilationJob::CollectRetainedMaps(
487  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Code> code) {
488  DCHECK(code->is_optimized_code());
489 
490  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
491  GlobalHandleVector<Map> maps(isolate->heap());
492  PtrComprCageBase cage_base(isolate);
493  int const mode_mask = RelocInfo::EmbeddedObjectModeMask();
494  for (RelocIterator it(*code, mode_mask); !it.done(); it.next()) {
495  DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsEmbeddedObjectMode(it.rinfo()->rmode()));
496  Tagged<HeapObject> target_object = it.rinfo()->target_object(cage_base);
497  if (code->IsWeakObjectInOptimizedCode(target_object)) {
498  if (IsMap(target_object, cage_base)) {
499  maps.Push(Cast<Map>(target_object));
500  }
501  }
502  }
503  return maps;
504 }
505 
506 void OptimizedCompilationJob::RegisterWeakObjectsInOptimizedCode(
507  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<NativeContext> context,
508  DirectHandle<Code> code, GlobalHandleVector<Map> maps) {
509  isolate->heap()->AddRetainedMaps(context, std::move(maps));
510  code->set_can_have_weak_objects(true);
511 }
512 
513 namespace {
514 uint64_t GetNextTraceId() {
515  // Define a global counter for optimized compile trace ids, which
516  // counts in the top 32 bits of a uint64_t. This will be mixed into
517  // the TurbofanCompilationJob `this` pointer, which hopefully will
518  // make the ids unique enough even when the job memory is reused
519  // for future jobs.
520  static std::atomic_uint32_t next_trace_id = 0xfa5701d0;
521  return static_cast<uint64_t>(next_trace_id++) << 32;
522 }
523 } // namespace
524 
525 TurbofanCompilationJob::TurbofanCompilationJob(
526  Isolate* isolate, OptimizedCompilationInfo* compilation_info,
527  State initial_state)
528  : OptimizedCompilationJob("Turbofan", initial_state),
529  isolate_(isolate),
530  compilation_info_(compilation_info),
531  trace_id_(GetNextTraceId() ^ reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(this)) {}
532 
533 CompilationJob::Status TurbofanCompilationJob::RetryOptimization(
534  BailoutReason reason) {
535  DCHECK(compilation_info_->IsOptimizing());
536  compilation_info_->RetryOptimization(reason);
537  return UpdateState(FAILED, State::kFailed);
538 }
539 
540 CompilationJob::Status TurbofanCompilationJob::AbortOptimization(
541  BailoutReason reason) {
542  DCHECK(compilation_info_->IsOptimizing());
543  compilation_info_->AbortOptimization(reason);
544  return UpdateState(FAILED, State::kFailed);
545 }
546 
547 void TurbofanCompilationJob::Cancel() { compilation_info_->mark_cancelled(); }
548 
549 void TurbofanCompilationJob::RecordCompilationStats(ConcurrencyMode mode,
550  Isolate* isolate) const {
551  DCHECK(compilation_info()->IsOptimizing());
552  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = compilation_info()->shared_info();
553  if (v8_flags.trace_opt || v8_flags.trace_opt_stats) {
554  double ms_creategraph = time_taken_to_prepare_.InMillisecondsF();
555  double ms_optimize = time_taken_to_execute_.InMillisecondsF();
556  double ms_codegen = time_taken_to_finalize_.InMillisecondsF();
557  if (v8_flags.trace_opt) {
558  CompilerTracer::TraceFinishTurbofanCompile(
559  isolate, compilation_info(), ms_creategraph, ms_optimize, ms_codegen);
560  }
561  if (v8_flags.trace_opt_stats) {
562  static double compilation_time = 0.0;
563  static int compiled_functions = 0;
564  static int code_size = 0;
565 
566  compilation_time += (ms_creategraph + ms_optimize + ms_codegen);
567  compiled_functions++;
568  code_size += shared->SourceSize();
569  PrintF(
570  "[turbofan] Compiled: %d functions with %d byte source size in "
571  "%fms.\n",
572  compiled_functions, code_size, compilation_time);
573  }
574  }
575  // Don't record samples from machines without high-resolution timers,
576  // as that can cause serious reporting issues. See the thread at
577  // http://g/chrome-metrics-team/NwwJEyL8odU/discussion for more details.
578  if (!base::TimeTicks::IsHighResolution()) return;
579 
580  int elapsed_microseconds = static_cast<int>(ElapsedTime().InMicroseconds());
581  Counters* const counters = isolate->counters();
582  counters->turbofan_ticks()->AddSample(static_cast<int>(
583  compilation_info()->tick_counter().CurrentTicks() / 1000));
584 
585  if (compilation_info()->is_osr()) {
586  counters->turbofan_osr_prepare()->AddSample(
587  static_cast<int>(time_taken_to_prepare_.InMicroseconds()));
588  counters->turbofan_osr_execute()->AddSample(
589  static_cast<int>(time_taken_to_execute_.InMicroseconds()));
590  counters->turbofan_osr_finalize()->AddSample(
591  static_cast<int>(time_taken_to_finalize_.InMicroseconds()));
592  counters->turbofan_osr_total_time()->AddSample(elapsed_microseconds);
593  return;
594  }
595 
596  DCHECK(!compilation_info()->is_osr());
597  counters->turbofan_optimize_prepare()->AddSample(
598  static_cast<int>(time_taken_to_prepare_.InMicroseconds()));
599  counters->turbofan_optimize_execute()->AddSample(
600  static_cast<int>(time_taken_to_execute_.InMicroseconds()));
601  counters->turbofan_optimize_finalize()->AddSample(
602  static_cast<int>(time_taken_to_finalize_.InMicroseconds()));
603  counters->turbofan_optimize_total_time()->AddSample(elapsed_microseconds);
604 
605  // Compute foreground / background time.
606  base::TimeDelta time_background;
607  base::TimeDelta time_foreground =
608  time_taken_to_prepare_ + time_taken_to_finalize_;
609  switch (mode) {
610  case ConcurrencyMode::kConcurrent:
611  time_background += time_taken_to_execute_;
612  counters->turbofan_optimize_concurrent_total_time()->AddSample(
613  elapsed_microseconds);
614  break;
615  case ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous:
616  counters->turbofan_optimize_non_concurrent_total_time()->AddSample(
617  elapsed_microseconds);
618  time_foreground += time_taken_to_execute_;
619  break;
620  }
621  counters->turbofan_optimize_total_background()->AddSample(
622  static_cast<int>(time_background.InMicroseconds()));
623  counters->turbofan_optimize_total_foreground()->AddSample(
624  static_cast<int>(time_foreground.InMicroseconds()));
625 
626  if (v8_flags.profile_guided_optimization &&
627  shared->cached_tiering_decision() ==
628  CachedTieringDecision::kEarlyMaglev) {
629  shared->set_cached_tiering_decision(CachedTieringDecision::kEarlyTurbofan);
630  }
631 }
632 
633 void TurbofanCompilationJob::RecordFunctionCompilation(
634  LogEventListener::CodeTag code_type, Isolate* isolate) const {
635  DirectHandle<AbstractCode> abstract_code =
636  Cast<AbstractCode>(compilation_info()->code());
637 
638  double time_taken_ms = time_taken_to_prepare_.InMillisecondsF() +
639  time_taken_to_execute_.InMillisecondsF() +
640  time_taken_to_finalize_.InMillisecondsF();
641 
642  DirectHandle<Script> script(
643  Cast<Script>(compilation_info()->shared_info()->script()), isolate);
644  DirectHandle<FeedbackVector> feedback_vector(
645  compilation_info()->closure()->feedback_vector(), isolate);
646  Compiler::LogFunctionCompilation(
647  isolate, code_type, script, compilation_info()->shared_info(),
648  feedback_vector, abstract_code, compilation_info()->code_kind(),
649  time_taken_ms);
650 }
651 
652 uint64_t TurbofanCompilationJob::trace_id() const {
653  // Xor together the this pointer and the optimization id, to try to make the
654  // id more unique on platforms where just the `this` pointer is likely to be
655  // reused.
656  return trace_id_;
657 }

659 // ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
660 // Local helper methods that make up the compilation pipeline.

662 namespace {
663 
664 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
665 bool UseAsmWasm(FunctionLiteral* literal, bool asm_wasm_broken) {
666  // Check whether asm.js validation is enabled.
667  if (!v8_flags.validate_asm) return false;
668 
669  // Modules that have validated successfully, but were subsequently broken by
670  // invalid module instantiation attempts are off limit forever.
671  if (asm_wasm_broken) return false;
672 
673  // In stress mode we want to run the validator on everything.
674  if (v8_flags.stress_validate_asm) return true;
675 
676  // In general, we respect the "use asm" directive.
677  return literal->scope()->IsAsmModule();
678 }
679 #endif
680 
681 } // namespace
682 
683 void Compiler::InstallInterpreterTrampolineCopy(
684  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info,
685  LogEventListener::CodeTag log_tag) {
686  DCHECK(isolate->interpreted_frames_native_stack());
687  if (!IsBytecodeArray(shared_info->GetTrustedData(isolate))) {
688  DCHECK(!shared_info->HasInterpreterData(isolate));
689  return;
690  }
691  DirectHandle<BytecodeArray> bytecode_array(
692  shared_info->GetBytecodeArray(isolate), isolate);
693 
694  DirectHandle<Code> code =
695  Builtins::CreateInterpreterEntryTrampolineForProfiling(isolate);
696 
697  DirectHandle<InterpreterData> interpreter_data =
698  isolate->factory()->NewInterpreterData(bytecode_array, code);
699 
700  if (shared_info->HasBaselineCode()) {
701  shared_info->baseline_code(kAcquireLoad)
702  ->set_bytecode_or_interpreter_data(*interpreter_data);
703  } else {
704  // IsBytecodeArray
705  shared_info->set_interpreter_data(isolate, *interpreter_data);
706  }
707 
708  DirectHandle<Script> script(Cast<Script>(shared_info->script()), isolate);
709  DirectHandle<AbstractCode> abstract_code = Cast<AbstractCode>(code);
710  Script::PositionInfo info;
711  Script::GetPositionInfo(script, shared_info->StartPosition(), &info);
712  int line_num = info.line + 1;
713  int column_num = info.column + 1;
714  DirectHandle<String> script_name(IsString(script->name())
715  ? Cast<String>(script->name())
716  : ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_string(),
717  isolate);
718  PROFILE(isolate, CodeCreateEvent(log_tag, abstract_code, shared_info,
719  script_name, line_num, column_num));
720 }
721 
722 namespace {
723 
724 template <typename IsolateT>
725 void InstallUnoptimizedCode(UnoptimizedCompilationInfo* compilation_info,
726  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info,
727  IsolateT* isolate) {
728  if (compilation_info->has_bytecode_array()) {
729  DCHECK(!shared_info->HasBytecodeArray()); // Only compiled once.
730  DCHECK(!compilation_info->has_asm_wasm_data());
731  DCHECK(!shared_info->HasFeedbackMetadata());
732 
733 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
734  // If the function failed asm-wasm compilation, mark asm_wasm as broken
735  // to ensure we don't try to compile as asm-wasm.
736  if (compilation_info->literal()->scope()->IsAsmModule()) {
737  shared_info->set_is_asm_wasm_broken(true);
738  }
739 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
740 
741  DirectHandle<FeedbackMetadata> feedback_metadata = FeedbackMetadata::New(
742  isolate, compilation_info->feedback_vector_spec());
743  shared_info->set_feedback_metadata(*feedback_metadata, kReleaseStore);
744 
745  shared_info->set_age(0);
746  shared_info->set_bytecode_array(*compilation_info->bytecode_array());
747  } else {
748 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
749  DCHECK(compilation_info->has_asm_wasm_data());
750  // We should only have asm/wasm data when finalizing on the main thread.
751  DCHECK((std::is_same_v<IsolateT, Isolate>));
752  shared_info->set_asm_wasm_data(*compilation_info->asm_wasm_data());
753  shared_info->set_feedback_metadata(
754  ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_feedback_metadata(), kReleaseStore);
755 #else
756  UNREACHABLE();
757 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
758  }
759 }
760 
761 template <typename IsolateT>
762 void EnsureInfosArrayOnScript(DirectHandle<Script> script,
763  ParseInfo* parse_info, IsolateT* isolate) {
764  DCHECK(parse_info->flags().is_toplevel());
765  if (script->infos()->length() > 0) {
766  DCHECK_EQ(script->infos()->length(), parse_info->max_info_id() + 1);
767  return;
768  }
769  DirectHandle<WeakFixedArray> infos(isolate->factory()->NewWeakFixedArray(
770  parse_info->max_info_id() + 1, AllocationType::kOld));
771  script->set_infos(*infos);
772 }
773 
774 void UpdateSharedFunctionFlagsAfterCompilation(FunctionLiteral* literal) {
775  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info = *literal->shared_function_info();
776  DCHECK_EQ(shared_info->language_mode(), literal->language_mode());
777 
778  // These fields are all initialised in ParseInfo from the SharedFunctionInfo,
779  // and then set back on the literal after parse. Hence, they should already
780  // match.
781  DCHECK_EQ(shared_info->requires_instance_members_initializer(),
782  literal->requires_instance_members_initializer());
783  DCHECK_EQ(shared_info->class_scope_has_private_brand(),
784  literal->class_scope_has_private_brand());
785  DCHECK_EQ(shared_info->has_static_private_methods_or_accessors(),
786  literal->has_static_private_methods_or_accessors());
787 
788  shared_info->set_has_duplicate_parameters(
789  literal->has_duplicate_parameters());
790  shared_info->UpdateAndFinalizeExpectedNofPropertiesFromEstimate(literal);
791 
792  shared_info->SetScopeInfo(*literal->scope()->scope_info());
793 }
794 
795 // Finalize a single compilation job. This function can return
796 // RETRY_ON_MAIN_THREAD if the job cannot be finalized off-thread, in which case
797 // it should be safe to call it again on the main thread with the same job.
798 template <typename IsolateT>
799 CompilationJob::Status FinalizeSingleUnoptimizedCompilationJob(
800  UnoptimizedCompilationJob* job, Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info,
801  IsolateT* isolate,
802  FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationDataList*
803  finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list) {
804  UnoptimizedCompilationInfo* compilation_info = job->compilation_info();
805 
806  CompilationJob::Status status = job->FinalizeJob(shared_info, isolate);
807  if (status == CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED) {
808  InstallUnoptimizedCode(compilation_info, shared_info, isolate);
809 
810  MaybeHandle<CoverageInfo> coverage_info;
811  if (compilation_info->has_coverage_info()) {
812  MutexGuardIfOffThread<IsolateT> mutex_guard(
813  isolate->shared_function_info_access(), isolate);
814  if (!shared_info->HasCoverageInfo(
815  isolate->GetMainThreadIsolateUnsafe())) {
816  coverage_info = compilation_info->coverage_info();
817  }
818  }
819 
820  finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list->emplace_back(
821  isolate, shared_info, coverage_info, job->time_taken_to_execute(),
822  job->time_taken_to_finalize());
823  }
824  DCHECK_IMPLIES(status == CompilationJob::RETRY_ON_MAIN_THREAD,
825  (std::is_same_v<IsolateT, LocalIsolate>));
826  return status;
827 }
828 
829 std::unique_ptr<UnoptimizedCompilationJob>
830 ExecuteSingleUnoptimizedCompilationJob(
831  ParseInfo* parse_info, FunctionLiteral* literal, Handle<Script> script,
832  AccountingAllocator* allocator,
833  std::vector<FunctionLiteral*>* eager_inner_literals,
834  LocalIsolate* local_isolate) {
835 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
836  if (UseAsmWasm(literal, parse_info->flags().is_asm_wasm_broken())) {
837  std::unique_ptr<UnoptimizedCompilationJob> asm_job(
838  AsmJs::NewCompilationJob(parse_info, literal, allocator));
839  if (asm_job->ExecuteJob() == CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED) {
840  return asm_job;
841  }
842  // asm.js validation failed, fall through to standard unoptimized compile.
843  // Note: we rely on the fact that AsmJs jobs have done all validation in the
844  // PrepareJob and ExecuteJob phases and can't fail in FinalizeJob with
845  // with a validation error or another error that could be solve by falling
846  // through to standard unoptimized compile.
847  }
848 #endif
849  std::unique_ptr<UnoptimizedCompilationJob> job(
850  interpreter::Interpreter::NewCompilationJob(
851  parse_info, literal, script, allocator, eager_inner_literals,
852  local_isolate));
853 
854  if (job->ExecuteJob() != CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED) {
855  // Compilation failed, return null.
856  return std::unique_ptr<UnoptimizedCompilationJob>();
857  }
858 
859  return job;
860 }
861 
862 template <typename IsolateT>
863 bool IterativelyExecuteAndFinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationJobs(
864  IsolateT* isolate, Handle<Script> script, ParseInfo* parse_info,
865  AccountingAllocator* allocator, IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope,
866  FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationDataList*
867  finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list,
868  DeferredFinalizationJobDataList*
869  jobs_to_retry_finalization_on_main_thread) {
870  DeclarationScope::AllocateScopeInfos(parse_info, script, isolate);
871 
872  std::vector<FunctionLiteral*> functions_to_compile;
873  functions_to_compile.push_back(parse_info->literal());
874 
875  bool compilation_succeeded = true;
876  while (!functions_to_compile.empty()) {
877  FunctionLiteral* literal = functions_to_compile.back();
878  functions_to_compile.pop_back();
879  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info = literal->shared_function_info();
880  // It's possible that compilation of an outer function overflowed the stack,
881  // so a literal we'd like to compile won't have its SFI yet. Skip compiling
882  // the inner function in that case.
883  if (shared_info.is_null()) continue;
884  if (shared_info->is_compiled()) continue;
885 
886  std::unique_ptr<UnoptimizedCompilationJob> job =
887  ExecuteSingleUnoptimizedCompilationJob(parse_info, literal, script,
888  allocator, &functions_to_compile,
889  isolate->AsLocalIsolate());
890 
891  if (!job) {
892  // Compilation failed presumably because of stack overflow, make sure
893  // the shared function info contains uncompiled data for the next
894  // compilation attempts.
895  if (!shared_info->HasUncompiledData(isolate)) {
896  SharedFunctionInfo::CreateAndSetUncompiledData(isolate, literal);
897  }
898  compilation_succeeded = false;
899  // Proceed finalizing other functions in case they don't have uncompiled
900  // data.
901  continue;
902  }
903 
904  UpdateSharedFunctionFlagsAfterCompilation(literal);
905 
906  auto finalization_status = FinalizeSingleUnoptimizedCompilationJob(
907  job.get(), shared_info, isolate,
908  finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list);
909 
910  switch (finalization_status) {
911  case CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED:
912  if (literal == parse_info->literal()) {
913  // Ensure that the top level function is retained.
914  *is_compiled_scope = shared_info->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
915  DCHECK(is_compiled_scope->is_compiled());
916  }
917  break;
918 
919  case CompilationJob::FAILED:
920  compilation_succeeded = false;
921  // Proceed finalizing other functions in case they don't have uncompiled
922  // data.
923  continue;
924 
925  case CompilationJob::RETRY_ON_MAIN_THREAD:
926  // This should not happen on the main thread.
927  DCHECK((!std::is_same_v<IsolateT, Isolate>));
928  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(jobs_to_retry_finalization_on_main_thread);
929 
930  // Clear the literal and ParseInfo to prevent further attempts to
931  // access them.
932  job->compilation_info()->ClearLiteral();
933  job->ClearParseInfo();
934  jobs_to_retry_finalization_on_main_thread->emplace_back(
935  isolate, shared_info, std::move(job));
936  break;
937  }
938  }
939 
940  // Report any warnings generated during compilation.
941  if (parse_info->pending_error_handler()->has_pending_warnings()) {
942  parse_info->pending_error_handler()->PrepareWarnings(isolate);
943  }
944 
945  return compilation_succeeded;
946 }
947 
948 bool FinalizeDeferredUnoptimizedCompilationJobs(
949  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Script> script,
950  DeferredFinalizationJobDataList* deferred_jobs,
951  PendingCompilationErrorHandler* pending_error_handler,
952  FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationDataList*
953  finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list) {
954  DCHECK(AllowCompilation::IsAllowed(isolate));
955 
956  if (deferred_jobs->empty()) return true;
957 
958  // TODO(rmcilroy): Clear native context in debug once AsmJS generates doesn't
959  // rely on accessing native context during finalization.
960 
961  // Finalize the deferred compilation jobs.
962  for (auto&& job : *deferred_jobs) {
963  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info = job.function_handle();
964  if (FinalizeSingleUnoptimizedCompilationJob(
965  job.job(), shared_info, isolate,
966  finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list) !=
967  CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED) {
968  return false;
969  }
970  }
971 
972  // Report any warnings generated during deferred finalization.
973  if (pending_error_handler->has_pending_warnings()) {
974  pending_error_handler->PrepareWarnings(isolate);
975  }
976 
977  return true;
978 }
979 
980 // A wrapper to access the optimized code cache slots on the feedback vector.
981 class OptimizedCodeCache : public AllStatic {
982  public:
983  static V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT MaybeHandle<Code> Get(
984  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
985  BytecodeOffset osr_offset, CodeKind code_kind) {
986  DCHECK_IMPLIES(V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL, IsOSR(osr_offset));
987  if (!CodeKindIsStoredInOptimizedCodeCache(code_kind)) return {};
988  if (!function->has_feedback_vector()) return {};
989 
990  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
991  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = function->shared();
992  RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileGetFromOptimizedCodeMap);
993 
994  Tagged<Code> code;
995  Tagged<FeedbackVector> feedback_vector = function->feedback_vector();
996  if (IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
997  Handle<BytecodeArray> bytecode(shared->GetBytecodeArray(isolate),
998  isolate);
999  interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator it(bytecode, osr_offset.ToInt());
1000  // Bytecode may be different, so make sure we're at a valid OSR entry.
1001  SBXCHECK(it.CurrentBytecodeIsValidOSREntry());
1002  std::optional<Tagged<Code>> maybe_code =
1003  feedback_vector->GetOptimizedOsrCode(isolate, bytecode,
1004  it.GetSlotOperand(2));
1005  if (maybe_code.has_value()) code = maybe_code.value();
1006  } else {
1007 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1008  UNREACHABLE();
1009 #else
1010  feedback_vector->EvictOptimizedCodeMarkedForDeoptimization(
1011  isolate, shared, "OptimizedCodeCache::Get");
1012  code = feedback_vector->optimized_code(isolate);
1013 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1014  }
1015 
1016  // Normal tierup should never request a code-kind we already have. In case
1017  // of OSR it can happen that we OSR from ignition to turbofan. This is
1018  // explicitly allowed here by reusing any larger-kinded than requested
1019  // code.
1020  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!code.is_null() && code->kind() > code_kind,
1021  IsOSR(osr_offset));
1022  if (code.is_null() || code->kind() < code_kind) return {};
1023 
1024  DCHECK(!code->marked_for_deoptimization());
1025  DCHECK(shared->is_compiled());
1026  DCHECK(CodeKindIsStoredInOptimizedCodeCache(code->kind()));
1027  DCHECK_IMPLIES(IsOSR(osr_offset), CodeKindCanOSR(code->kind()));
1028 
1029  CompilerTracer::TraceOptimizedCodeCacheHit(isolate, function, osr_offset,
1030  code_kind);
1031  return handle(code, isolate);
1032  }
1033 
1034  static void Insert(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSFunction> function,
1035  BytecodeOffset osr_offset, Tagged<Code> code,
1036  bool is_function_context_specializing) {
1037  DCHECK_IMPLIES(V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL, IsOSR(osr_offset));
1038  const CodeKind kind = code->kind();
1039  if (!CodeKindIsStoredInOptimizedCodeCache(kind)) return;
1040 
1041  Tagged<FeedbackVector> feedback_vector = function->feedback_vector();
1042 
1043  if (IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
1044  DCHECK(CodeKindCanOSR(kind));
1045  DCHECK(!is_function_context_specializing);
1046  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = function->shared();
1047  Handle<BytecodeArray> bytecode(shared->GetBytecodeArray(isolate),
1048  isolate);
1049  interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator it(bytecode, osr_offset.ToInt());
1050  // Bytecode may be different, so make sure we're at a valid OSR entry.
1051  SBXCHECK(it.CurrentBytecodeIsValidOSREntry());
1052  feedback_vector->SetOptimizedOsrCode(isolate, it.GetSlotOperand(2), code);
1053  return;
1054  }
1055 
1056 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1057  UNREACHABLE();
1058 #else
1059  DCHECK(!IsOSR(osr_offset));
1060 
1061  if (is_function_context_specializing) {
1062  // Function context specialization folds-in the function context, so no
1063  // sharing can occur. Make sure the optimized code cache is cleared.
1064  // Only do so if the specialized code's kind matches the cached code kind.
1065  if (feedback_vector->has_optimized_code() &&
1066  feedback_vector->optimized_code(isolate)->kind() == code->kind()) {
1067  feedback_vector->ClearOptimizedCode();
1068  }
1069  return;
1070  }
1071 
1072  function->shared()->set_function_context_independent_compiled(true);
1073  feedback_vector->SetOptimizedCode(isolate, code);
1074 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1075  }
1076 };
1077 
1078 // Runs PrepareJob in the proper compilation scopes. Handles will be allocated
1079 // in a persistent handle scope that is detached and handed off to the
1080 // {compilation_info} after PrepareJob.
1081 bool PrepareJobWithHandleScope(OptimizedCompilationJob* job, Isolate* isolate,
1082  OptimizedCompilationInfo* compilation_info,
1083  ConcurrencyMode mode) {
1084  CompilationHandleScope compilation(isolate, compilation_info);
1085  CompilerTracer::TracePrepareJob(isolate, compilation_info, mode);
1086  compilation_info->ReopenAndCanonicalizeHandlesInNewScope(isolate);
1087  return job->PrepareJob(isolate) == CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED;
1088 }
1089 
1090 bool CompileTurbofan_NotConcurrent(Isolate* isolate,
1091  TurbofanCompilationJob* job) {
1092  OptimizedCompilationInfo* const compilation_info = job->compilation_info();
1093  DCHECK_EQ(compilation_info->code_kind(), CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS);
1094 
1095  TimerEventScope<TimerEventRecompileSynchronous> timer(isolate);
1096  RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kOptimizeSynchronous);
1097  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
1098  "V8.OptimizeNonConcurrent");
1099 
1100  if (!PrepareJobWithHandleScope(job, isolate, compilation_info,
1101  ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous)) {
1102  CompilerTracer::TraceAbortedJob(isolate, compilation_info,
1103  job->prepare_in_ms(), job->execute_in_ms(),
1104  job->finalize_in_ms());
1105  return false;
1106  }
1107 
1108  if (job->ExecuteJob(isolate->counters()->runtime_call_stats(),
1109  isolate->main_thread_local_isolate())) {
1110  CompilerTracer::TraceAbortedJob(isolate, compilation_info,
1111  job->prepare_in_ms(), job->execute_in_ms(),
1112  job->finalize_in_ms());
1113  return false;
1114  }
1115 
1116  if (job->FinalizeJob(isolate) != CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED) {
1117  CompilerTracer::TraceAbortedJob(isolate, compilation_info,
1118  job->prepare_in_ms(), job->execute_in_ms(),
1119  job->finalize_in_ms());
1120  return false;
1121  }
1122 
1123  // Success!
1124  job->RecordCompilationStats(ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous, isolate);
1125  DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
1126  if (!V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL || job->compilation_info()->is_osr()) {
1127  OptimizedCodeCache::Insert(
1128  isolate, *compilation_info->closure(), compilation_info->osr_offset(),
1129  *compilation_info->code(),
1130  compilation_info->function_context_specializing());
1131  }
1132  job->RecordFunctionCompilation(LogEventListener::CodeTag::kFunction, isolate);
1133  return true;
1134 }
1135 
1136 bool CompileTurbofan_Concurrent(Isolate* isolate,
1137  std::unique_ptr<TurbofanCompilationJob> job) {
1138  OptimizedCompilationInfo* const compilation_info = job->compilation_info();
1139  DCHECK_EQ(compilation_info->code_kind(), CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS);
1140  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function = compilation_info->closure();
1141 
1142  if (!isolate->optimizing_compile_dispatcher()->IsQueueAvailable()) {
1143  if (v8_flags.trace_concurrent_recompilation) {
1144  PrintF(" ** Compilation queue full, will retry optimizing ");
1145  ShortPrint(*function);
1146  PrintF(" later.\n");
1147  }
1148  return false;
1149  }
1150 
1151  if (isolate->heap()->HighMemoryPressure()) {
1152  if (v8_flags.trace_concurrent_recompilation) {
1153  PrintF(" ** High memory pressure, will retry optimizing ");
1154  ShortPrint(*function);
1155  PrintF(" later.\n");
1156  }
1157  return false;
1158  }
1159 
1160  TimerEventScope<TimerEventRecompileSynchronous> timer(isolate);
1161  RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kOptimizeConcurrentPrepare);
1162  TRACE_EVENT_WITH_FLOW0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
1163  "V8.OptimizeConcurrentPrepare", job->trace_id(),
1164  TRACE_EVENT_FLAG_FLOW_OUT);
1165 
1166  if (!PrepareJobWithHandleScope(job.get(), isolate, compilation_info,
1167  ConcurrencyMode::kConcurrent)) {
1168  return false;
1169  }
1170 
1171  if (V8_LIKELY(!compilation_info->discard_result_for_testing())) {
1172  function->SetTieringInProgress(isolate, true,
1173  compilation_info->osr_offset());
1174  }
1175 
1176  // The background recompile will own this job.
1177  if (!isolate->optimizing_compile_dispatcher()->TryQueueForOptimization(job)) {
1178  function->SetTieringInProgress(isolate, false,
1179  compilation_info->osr_offset());
1180 
1181  if (v8_flags.trace_concurrent_recompilation) {
1182  PrintF(" ** Compilation queue full, will retry optimizing ");
1183  ShortPrint(*function);
1184  PrintF(" later.\n");
1185  }
1186  return false;
1187  }
1188 
1189  if (v8_flags.trace_concurrent_recompilation) {
1190  PrintF(" ** Queued ");
1191  ShortPrint(*function);
1192  PrintF(" for concurrent optimization.\n");
1193  }
1194 
1195  DCHECK(compilation_info->shared_info()->HasBytecodeArray());
1196  return true;
1197 }
1198 
1199 enum class CompileResultBehavior {
1200  // Default behavior, i.e. install the result, insert into caches, etc.
1201  kDefault,
1202  // Used only for stress testing. The compilation result should be discarded.
1203  kDiscardForTesting,
1204 };
1205 
1206 bool ShouldOptimize(CodeKind code_kind,
1207  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared) {
1208  DCHECK(CodeKindIsOptimizedJSFunction(code_kind));
1209  switch (code_kind) {
1210  case CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS:
1211  return v8_flags.turbofan && shared->PassesFilter(v8_flags.turbo_filter);
1212  case CodeKind::MAGLEV:
1213  return maglev::IsMaglevEnabled() &&
1214  shared->PassesFilter(v8_flags.maglev_filter);
1215  default:
1216  UNREACHABLE();
1217  }
1218 }
1219 
1220 MaybeHandle<Code> CompileTurbofan(Isolate* isolate, Handle<JSFunction> function,
1221  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
1222  ConcurrencyMode mode,
1223  BytecodeOffset osr_offset,
1224  CompileResultBehavior result_behavior) {
1225  VMState<COMPILER> state(isolate);
1226  TimerEventScope<TimerEventOptimizeCode> optimize_code_timer(isolate);
1227  RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kOptimizeCode);
1228  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"), "V8.OptimizeCode");
1229 
1230  DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
1231  PostponeInterruptsScope postpone(isolate);
1232  const compiler::IsScriptAvailable has_script =
1233  IsScript(shared->script()) ? compiler::IsScriptAvailable::kYes
1234  : compiler::IsScriptAvailable::kNo;
1235  // BUG(5946): This DCHECK is necessary to make certain that we won't
1236  // tolerate the lack of a script without bytecode.
1237  DCHECK_IMPLIES(has_script == compiler::IsScriptAvailable::kNo,
1238  shared->HasBytecodeArray());
1239  std::unique_ptr<TurbofanCompilationJob> job(
1240  compiler::NewCompilationJob(isolate, function, has_script, osr_offset));
1241 
1242  if (result_behavior == CompileResultBehavior::kDiscardForTesting) {
1243  job->compilation_info()->set_discard_result_for_testing();
1244  }
1245 
1246  if (IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
1247  isolate->CountUsage(v8::Isolate::kTurboFanOsrCompileStarted);
1248  }
1249 
1250  // Prepare the job and launch concurrent compilation, or compile now.
1251  if (IsConcurrent(mode)) {
1252  if (CompileTurbofan_Concurrent(isolate, std::move(job))) return {};
1253  } else {
1254  DCHECK(IsSynchronous(mode));
1255  if (CompileTurbofan_NotConcurrent(isolate, job.get())) {
1256  return job->compilation_info()->code();
1257  }
1258  }
1259 
1260  if (isolate->has_exception()) isolate->clear_exception();
1261  return {};
1262 }
1263 
1264 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
1265 // TODO(v8:7700): Record maglev compilations better.
1266 void RecordMaglevFunctionCompilation(Isolate* isolate,
1267  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
1268  DirectHandle<AbstractCode> code) {
1269  PtrComprCageBase cage_base(isolate);
1270  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(function->shared(cage_base), isolate);
1271  DirectHandle<Script> script(Cast<Script>(shared->script(cage_base)), isolate);
1272  DirectHandle<FeedbackVector> feedback_vector(
1273  function->feedback_vector(cage_base), isolate);
1274 
1275  // Optimistic estimate.
1276  double time_taken_ms = 0;
1277 
1278  Compiler::LogFunctionCompilation(
1279  isolate, LogEventListener::CodeTag::kFunction, script, shared,
1280  feedback_vector, code, code->kind(cage_base), time_taken_ms);
1281 }
1282 #endif // V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
1283 
1284 MaybeHandle<Code> CompileMaglev(Isolate* isolate, Handle<JSFunction> function,
1285  ConcurrencyMode mode, BytecodeOffset osr_offset,
1286  CompileResultBehavior result_behavior) {
1287 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
1288  DCHECK(maglev::IsMaglevEnabled());
1289  CHECK(result_behavior == CompileResultBehavior::kDefault);
1290 
1291  // TODO(v8:7700): Tracing, see CompileTurbofan.
1292 
1293  DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
1294  PostponeInterruptsScope postpone(isolate);
1295 
1296  // TODO(v8:7700): See everything in CompileTurbofan_Concurrent.
1297  // - Tracing,
1298  // - timers,
1299  // - aborts on memory pressure,
1300  // ...
1301 
1302  // Prepare the job.
1303  auto job = maglev::MaglevCompilationJob::New(isolate, function, osr_offset);
1304 
1305  if (IsConcurrent(mode) &&
1306  !isolate->maglev_concurrent_dispatcher()->is_enabled()) {
1307  mode = ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous;
1308  }
1309 
1310  {
1311  TRACE_EVENT_WITH_FLOW0(
1312  TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
1313  IsSynchronous(mode) ? "V8.MaglevPrepare" : "V8.MaglevConcurrentPrepare",
1314  job->trace_id(), TRACE_EVENT_FLAG_FLOW_OUT);
1315  CompilerTracer::TraceStartMaglevCompile(isolate, function, job->is_osr(),
1316  mode);
1317  CompilationJob::Status status = job->PrepareJob(isolate);
1318  CHECK_EQ(status, CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED); // TODO(v8:7700): Use status.
1319  }
1320 
1321  if (IsSynchronous(mode)) {
1322  CompilationJob::Status status =
1323  job->ExecuteJob(isolate->counters()->runtime_call_stats(),
1324  isolate->main_thread_local_isolate());
1325  if (status == CompilationJob::FAILED) {
1326  return {};
1327  }
1328  CHECK_EQ(status, CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED);
1329 
1330  Compiler::FinalizeMaglevCompilationJob(job.get(), isolate);
1331 
1332  return job->code();
1333  }
1334 
1335  DCHECK(IsConcurrent(mode));
1336 
1337  // Enqueue it.
1338  isolate->maglev_concurrent_dispatcher()->EnqueueJob(std::move(job));
1339 
1340  // Remember that the function is currently being processed.
1341  function->SetTieringInProgress(isolate, true, osr_offset);
1342  function->SetInterruptBudget(isolate, BudgetModification::kRaise,
1343  CodeKind::MAGLEV);
1344 
1345  return {};
1346 #else // V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
1347  UNREACHABLE();
1348 #endif // V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
1349 }
1350 
1351 MaybeHandle<Code> GetOrCompileOptimized(
1352  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> function, ConcurrencyMode mode,
1353  CodeKind code_kind, BytecodeOffset osr_offset = BytecodeOffset::None(),
1354  CompileResultBehavior result_behavior = CompileResultBehavior::kDefault) {
1355  if (IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
1356  function->TraceOptimizationStatus(
1357  "^%s (osr %i)", CodeKindToString(code_kind), osr_offset.ToInt());
1358  } else {
1359  function->TraceOptimizationStatus("^%s", CodeKindToString(code_kind));
1360  }
1361  DCHECK(CodeKindIsOptimizedJSFunction(code_kind));
1362 
1363  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(function->shared(), isolate);
1364 
1365  // Reset the OSR urgency. If we enter a function OSR should not be triggered.
1366  // If we are in fact in a loop we should avoid triggering this compilation
1367  // request on every iteration and thereby skipping other interrupts.
1368  function->feedback_vector()->reset_osr_urgency();
1369 
1370  // Clear the optimization marker on the function so that we don't try to
1371  // re-optimize.
1372  if (!IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
1373  function->ResetTieringRequests();
1374  // Always reset the OSR urgency to ensure we reset it on function entry.
1375  int invocation_count =
1376  function->feedback_vector()->invocation_count(kRelaxedLoad);
1377  if (!(V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.testing_d8_test_runner ||
1378  v8_flags.allow_natives_syntax) &&
1379  ManualOptimizationTable::IsMarkedForManualOptimization(isolate,
1380  *function)) &&
1381  invocation_count < v8_flags.minimum_invocations_before_optimization) {
1382  function->feedback_vector()->set_invocation_count(invocation_count + 1,
1383  kRelaxedStore);
1384  return {};
1385  }
1386  }
1387 
1388  if (shared->optimization_disabled(CodeKind::MAGLEV)) {
1389  return {};
1390  }
1391 
1392  // Do not optimize when debugger needs to hook into every call.
1393  if (isolate->debug()->needs_check_on_function_call()) {
1394  return {};
1395  }
1396 
1397  // Do not optimize if we need to be able to set break points.
1398  if (shared->HasBreakInfo(isolate)) return {};
1399 
1400  // Do not optimize if optimization is disabled or function doesn't pass
1401  // turbo_filter.
1402  if (!ShouldOptimize(code_kind, shared)) return {};
1403 
1404  if (!V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL || IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
1405  Handle<Code> cached_code;
1406  if (OptimizedCodeCache::Get(isolate, function, osr_offset, code_kind)
1407  .ToHandle(&cached_code)) {
1408  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!IsOSR(osr_offset), cached_code->kind() <= code_kind);
1409  return cached_code;
1410  }
1411 
1412  if (IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
1413  // One OSR job per function at a time.
1414  if (function->osr_tiering_in_progress()) return {};
1415  }
1416  }
1417 
1418  DCHECK(shared->is_compiled());
1419 
1420  if (code_kind == CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS) {
1421  return CompileTurbofan(isolate, indirect_handle(function, isolate), shared,
1422  mode, osr_offset, result_behavior);
1423  } else {
1424  DCHECK_EQ(code_kind, CodeKind::MAGLEV);
1425  return CompileMaglev(isolate, indirect_handle(function, isolate), mode,
1426  osr_offset, result_behavior);
1427  }
1428 }
1429 
1430 // When --stress-concurrent-inlining is enabled, spawn concurrent jobs in
1431 // addition to non-concurrent compiles to increase coverage in mjsunit tests
1432 // (where most interesting compiles are non-concurrent). The result of the
1433 // compilation is thrown out.
1434 void SpawnDuplicateConcurrentJobForStressTesting(
1435  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> function, ConcurrencyMode mode,
1436  CodeKind code_kind) {
1437  // TODO(v8:7700): Support Maglev.
1438  if (code_kind == CodeKind::MAGLEV) return;
1439 
1440  if (function->ActiveTierIsTurbofan(isolate)) return;
1441 
1442  DCHECK(v8_flags.stress_concurrent_inlining &&
1443  isolate->concurrent_recompilation_enabled() && IsSynchronous(mode) &&
1444  isolate->node_observer() == nullptr);
1445  CompileResultBehavior result_behavior =
1446  v8_flags.stress_concurrent_inlining_attach_code
1447  ? CompileResultBehavior::kDefault
1448  : CompileResultBehavior::kDiscardForTesting;
1449  USE(GetOrCompileOptimized(isolate, function, ConcurrencyMode::kConcurrent,
1450  code_kind, BytecodeOffset::None(),
1451  result_behavior));
1452 }
1453 
1454 bool FailAndClearException(Isolate* isolate) {
1455  isolate->clear_internal_exception();
1456  return false;
1457 }
1458 
1459 template <typename IsolateT>
1460 bool PrepareException(IsolateT* isolate, ParseInfo* parse_info) {
1461  if (parse_info->pending_error_handler()->has_pending_error()) {
1462  parse_info->pending_error_handler()->PrepareErrors(
1463  isolate, parse_info->ast_value_factory());
1464  }
1465  return false;
1466 }
1467 
1468 bool FailWithPreparedException(
1469  Isolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script,
1470  const PendingCompilationErrorHandler* pending_error_handler,
1471  Compiler::ClearExceptionFlag flag = Compiler::KEEP_EXCEPTION) {
1472  if (flag == Compiler::CLEAR_EXCEPTION) {
1473  return FailAndClearException(isolate);
1474  }
1475 
1476  if (!isolate->has_exception()) {
1477  if (pending_error_handler->has_pending_error()) {
1478  pending_error_handler->ReportErrors(isolate, script);
1479  } else {
1480  isolate->StackOverflow();
1481  }
1482  }
1483  return false;
1484 }
1485 
1486 bool FailWithException(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script,
1487  ParseInfo* parse_info,
1488  Compiler::ClearExceptionFlag flag) {
1489  PrepareException(isolate, parse_info);
1490  return FailWithPreparedException(isolate, script,
1491  parse_info->pending_error_handler(), flag);
1492 }
1493 
1494 void FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilation(
1495  Isolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script,
1496  const UnoptimizedCompileFlags& flags,
1497  const UnoptimizedCompileState* compile_state,
1498  const FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationDataList&
1499  finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list) {
1500  if (compile_state->pending_error_handler()->has_pending_warnings()) {
1501  compile_state->pending_error_handler()->ReportWarnings(isolate, script);
1502  }
1503 
1504  bool need_source_positions =
1505  v8_flags.stress_lazy_source_positions ||
1506  (!flags.collect_source_positions() && isolate->NeedsSourcePositions());
1507 
1508  for (const auto& finalize_data : finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list) {
1509  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info =
1510  finalize_data.function_handle();
1511  // It's unlikely, but possible, that the bytecode was flushed between being
1512  // allocated and now, so guard against that case, and against it being
1513  // flushed in the middle of this loop.
1514  IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope(*shared_info, isolate);
1515  if (!is_compiled_scope.is_compiled()) continue;
1516 
1517  if (need_source_positions) {
1518  SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(isolate, shared_info);
1519  }
1520  LogEventListener::CodeTag log_tag;
1521  if (shared_info->is_toplevel()) {
1522  log_tag = flags.is_eval() ? LogEventListener::CodeTag::kEval
1523  : LogEventListener::CodeTag::kScript;
1524  } else {
1525  log_tag = LogEventListener::CodeTag::kFunction;
1526  }
1527  log_tag = V8FileLogger::ToNativeByScript(log_tag, *script);
1528  if (isolate->interpreted_frames_native_stack() &&
1529  isolate->logger()->is_listening_to_code_events()) {
1530  Compiler::InstallInterpreterTrampolineCopy(isolate, shared_info, log_tag);
1531  }
1532  DirectHandle<CoverageInfo> coverage_info;
1533  if (finalize_data.coverage_info().ToHandle(&coverage_info)) {
1534  isolate->debug()->InstallCoverageInfo(shared_info, coverage_info);
1535  }
1536 
1537  LogUnoptimizedCompilation(isolate, shared_info, log_tag,
1538  finalize_data.time_taken_to_execute(),
1539  finalize_data.time_taken_to_finalize());
1540  }
1541 }
1542 
1543 void FinalizeUnoptimizedScriptCompilation(
1544  Isolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script,
1545  const UnoptimizedCompileFlags& flags,
1546  const UnoptimizedCompileState* compile_state,
1547  const FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationDataList&
1548  finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list) {
1549  FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilation(isolate, script, flags, compile_state,
1550  finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list);
1551 
1552  script->set_compilation_state(Script::CompilationState::kCompiled);
1553  DCHECK_IMPLIES(isolate->NeedsSourcePositions(), script->has_line_ends());
1554 }
1555 
1556 void CompileAllWithBaseline(Isolate* isolate,
1557  const FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationDataList&
1558  finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list) {
1559  for (const auto& finalize_data : finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list) {
1560  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info = finalize_data.function_handle();
1561  IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope(*shared_info, isolate);
1562  if (!is_compiled_scope.is_compiled()) continue;
1563  if (!CanCompileWithBaseline(isolate, *shared_info)) continue;
1564  Compiler::CompileSharedWithBaseline(
1565  isolate, shared_info, Compiler::CLEAR_EXCEPTION, &is_compiled_scope);
1566  }
1567 }
1568 
1569 // Create shared function info for top level and shared function infos array for
1570 // inner functions.
1571 template <typename IsolateT>
1572 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> CreateTopLevelSharedFunctionInfo(
1573  ParseInfo* parse_info, DirectHandle<Script> script, IsolateT* isolate) {
1574  EnsureInfosArrayOnScript(script, parse_info, isolate);
1575  DCHECK_EQ(kNoSourcePosition,
1576  parse_info->literal()->function_token_position());
1577  return isolate->factory()->NewSharedFunctionInfoForLiteral(
1578  parse_info->literal(), script, true);
1579 }
1580 
1581 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> GetOrCreateTopLevelSharedFunctionInfo(
1582  ParseInfo* parse_info, DirectHandle<Script> script, Isolate* isolate,
1583  IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope) {
1584  EnsureInfosArrayOnScript(script, parse_info, isolate);
1585  MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_shared =
1586  Script::FindSharedFunctionInfo(script, isolate, parse_info->literal());
1587  if (Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared; maybe_shared.ToHandle(&shared)) {
1588  DCHECK_EQ(shared->function_literal_id(kRelaxedLoad),
1589  parse_info->literal()->function_literal_id());
1590  *is_compiled_scope = shared->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
1591  return shared;
1592  }
1593  return CreateTopLevelSharedFunctionInfo(parse_info, script, isolate);
1594 }
1595 
1596 MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> CompileToplevel(
1597  ParseInfo* parse_info, Handle<Script> script,
1598  MaybeDirectHandle<ScopeInfo> maybe_outer_scope_info, Isolate* isolate,
1599  IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope) {
1600  TimerEventScope<TimerEventCompileCode> top_level_timer(isolate);
1601  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"), "V8.CompileCode");
1602  DCHECK_EQ(ThreadId::Current(), isolate->thread_id());
1603 
1604  PostponeInterruptsScope postpone(isolate);
1605  DCHECK(!isolate->native_context().is_null());
1606  RCS_SCOPE(isolate, parse_info->flags().is_eval()
1607  ? RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileEval
1608  : RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileScript);
1609  VMState<BYTECODE_COMPILER> state(isolate);
1610  if (parse_info->literal() == nullptr &&
1611  !parsing::ParseProgram(parse_info, script, maybe_outer_scope_info,
1612  isolate, parsing::ReportStatisticsMode::kYes)) {
1613  FailWithException(isolate, script, parse_info,
1614  Compiler::ClearExceptionFlag::KEEP_EXCEPTION);
1615  return MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo>();
1616  }
1617  // Measure how long it takes to do the compilation; only take the
1618  // rest of the function into account to avoid overlap with the
1619  // parsing statistics.
1620  NestedTimedHistogram* rate = parse_info->flags().is_eval()
1621  ? isolate->counters()->compile_eval()
1622  : isolate->counters()->compile();
1623  NestedTimedHistogramScope timer(rate);
1624  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
1625  parse_info->flags().is_eval() ? "V8.CompileEval" : "V8.Compile");
1626 
1627  // Create the SharedFunctionInfo and add it to the script's list.
1628  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info =
1629  GetOrCreateTopLevelSharedFunctionInfo(parse_info, script, isolate,
1630  is_compiled_scope);
1631 
1632  FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationDataList
1633  finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list;
1634 
1635  // Prepare and execute compilation of the outer-most function.
1636  if (!IterativelyExecuteAndFinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationJobs(
1637  isolate, script, parse_info, isolate->allocator(), is_compiled_scope,
1638  &finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list, nullptr)) {
1639  FailWithException(isolate, script, parse_info,
1640  Compiler::ClearExceptionFlag::KEEP_EXCEPTION);
1641  return MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo>();
1642  }
1643 
1644  // Character stream shouldn't be used again.
1645  parse_info->ResetCharacterStream();
1646 
1647  FinalizeUnoptimizedScriptCompilation(
1648  isolate, script, parse_info->flags(), parse_info->state(),
1649  finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list);
1650 
1651  if (v8_flags.always_sparkplug) {
1652  CompileAllWithBaseline(isolate, finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list);
1653  }
1654 
1655  return shared_info;
1656 }
1657 
1658 #ifdef V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
1659 RuntimeCallCounterId RuntimeCallCounterIdForCompile(ParseInfo* parse_info) {
1660  if (parse_info->flags().is_toplevel()) {
1661  if (parse_info->flags().is_eval()) {
1662  return RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileEval;
1663  }
1664  return RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileScript;
1665  }
1666  return RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileFunction;
1667 }
1668 #endif // V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS

1674 }

1687 DeferredFinalizationJobData::DeferredFinalizationJobData(

1714  compile_hint_callback_(compile_hint_callback),
1715  compile_hint_callback_data_(compile_hint_callback_data) {

1717  flags_.set_produce_compile_hints(true);
1718  }

1721  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(compile_hint_callback);
1722  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(compile_hint_callback_data);

1724  DCHECK_NULL(compile_hint_callback);

1728  options &
1729  ScriptCompiler::CompileOptions::kFollowCompileHintsMagicComment);

1766 void SetScriptFieldsFromDetails(Isolate* isolate, Tagged<Script> script,
1767  const ScriptDetails& script_details,
1768  DisallowGarbageCollection* no_gc) {
1769  Handle<Object> script_name;
1770  if (script_details.name_obj.ToHandle(&script_name)) {
1771  script->set_name(*script_name);
1772  script->set_line_offset(script_details.line_offset);
1773  script->set_column_offset(script_details.column_offset);
1774  }
1775  // The API can provide a source map URL, but a source map URL could also have
1776  // been inferred by the parser from a magic comment. The API source map URL
1777  // takes precedence (as long as it is a non-empty string).
1778  Handle<Object> source_map_url;
1779  if (script_details.source_map_url.ToHandle(&source_map_url) &&
1780  IsString(*source_map_url) &&
1781  Cast<String>(*source_map_url)->length() > 0) {
1782  script->set_source_mapping_url(*source_map_url);
1783  }
1784  Handle<Object> host_defined_options;
1785  if (script_details.host_defined_options.ToHandle(&host_defined_options)) {
1786  // TODO(cbruni, chromium:1244145): Remove once migrated to the context.
1787  if (IsFixedArray(*host_defined_options)) {
1788  script->set_host_defined_options(Cast<FixedArray>(*host_defined_options));
1789  }
1790  }
1791 }
