1793 namespace {
1794 
1795 #ifdef ENABLE_SLOW_DCHECKS
1796 
1797 // A class which traverses the object graph for a newly compiled Script and
1798 // ensures that it contains pointers to Scripts, ScopeInfos and
1799 // SharedFunctionInfos only at the expected locations. Any failure in this
1800 // visitor indicates a case that is probably not handled correctly in
1801 // BackgroundMergeTask.
1802 class MergeAssumptionChecker final : public ObjectVisitor {
1803  public:
1804  explicit MergeAssumptionChecker(LocalIsolate* isolate)
1805  : isolate_(isolate), cage_base_(isolate->cage_base()) {}
1806 
1807  void IterateObjects(Tagged<HeapObject> start) {
1808  QueueVisit(start, kNormalObject);
1809  while (to_visit_.size() > 0) {
1810  std::pair<Tagged<HeapObject>, ObjectKind> pair = to_visit_.top();
1811  to_visit_.pop();
1812  Tagged<HeapObject> current = pair.first;
1813  // The Script's infos list and the constant pools for all
1814  // BytecodeArrays are expected to contain pointers to SharedFunctionInfos.
1815  // However, the type of those objects (FixedArray or WeakFixedArray)
1816  // doesn't have enough information to indicate their usage, so we enqueue
1817  // those objects here rather than during VisitPointers.
1818  if (IsScript(current)) {
1819  Tagged<Script> script = Cast<Script>(current);
1820  Tagged<HeapObject> infos = script->infos();
1821  QueueVisit(infos, kScriptInfosList);
1822  // Avoid visiting eval_from_shared_or_wrapped_arguments. This field
1823  // points to data outside the new Script, and doesn't need to be merged.
1824  Tagged<HeapObject> eval_from_shared_or_wrapped_arguments;
1825  if (script->eval_from_shared_or_wrapped_arguments()
1826  .GetHeapObjectIfStrong(
1827  &eval_from_shared_or_wrapped_arguments)) {
1828  visited_.insert(eval_from_shared_or_wrapped_arguments);
1829  }
1830  } else if (IsBytecodeArray(current)) {
1831  Tagged<HeapObject> constants =
1832  Cast<BytecodeArray>(current)->constant_pool();
1833  QueueVisit(constants, kConstantPool);
1834  }
1835  current_object_kind_ = pair.second;
1836  i::VisitObjectBody(isolate_, current, this);
1837  QueueVisit(current->map(), kNormalObject);
1838  }
1839  }
1840 
1841  // ObjectVisitor implementation:
1842  void VisitPointers(Tagged<HeapObject> host, ObjectSlot start,
1843  ObjectSlot end) override {
1844  MaybeObjectSlot maybe_start(start);
1845  MaybeObjectSlot maybe_end(end);
1846  VisitPointers(host, maybe_start, maybe_end);
1847  }
1848  void VisitPointers(Tagged<HeapObject> host, MaybeObjectSlot start,
1849  MaybeObjectSlot end) override {
1850  for (MaybeObjectSlot current = start; current != end; ++current) {
1851  Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_obj = current.load(cage_base_);
1852  Tagged<HeapObject> obj;
1853  bool is_weak = maybe_obj.IsWeak();
1854  if (maybe_obj.GetHeapObject(&obj)) {
1855  if (IsSharedFunctionInfo(obj)) {
1856  CHECK((current_object_kind_ == kConstantPool && !is_weak) ||
1857  (current_object_kind_ == kScriptInfosList && is_weak) ||
1858  (IsScript(host) &&
1859  current.address() ==
1860  host.address() +
1861  Script::kEvalFromSharedOrWrappedArgumentsOffset));
1862  } else if (IsScopeInfo(obj)) {
1863  CHECK((current_object_kind_ == kConstantPool && !is_weak) ||
1864  (current_object_kind_ == kNormalObject && !is_weak) ||
1865  (current_object_kind_ == kScriptInfosList && is_weak));
1866  } else if (IsScript(obj)) {
1867  CHECK(IsSharedFunctionInfo(host) &&
1868  current == MaybeObjectSlot(host.address() +
1869  SharedFunctionInfo::kScriptOffset));
1870  } else if (IsFixedArray(obj) && current_object_kind_ == kConstantPool) {
1871  // Constant pools can contain nested fixed arrays, which in turn can
1872  // point to SFIs.
1873  QueueVisit(obj, kConstantPool);
1874  }
1875 
1876  QueueVisit(obj, kNormalObject);
1877  }
1878  }
1879  }
1880 
1881  // The object graph for a newly compiled Script shouldn't yet contain any
1882  // Code. If any of these functions are called, then that would indicate that
1883  // the graph was not disjoint from the rest of the heap as expected.
1884  void VisitInstructionStreamPointer(Tagged<Code> host,
1885  InstructionStreamSlot slot) override {
1886  UNREACHABLE();
1887  }
1888  void VisitCodeTarget(Tagged<InstructionStream> host,
1889  RelocInfo* rinfo) override {
1890  UNREACHABLE();
1891  }
1892  void VisitEmbeddedPointer(Tagged<InstructionStream> host,
1893  RelocInfo* rinfo) override {
1894  UNREACHABLE();
1895  }
1896 
1897  private:
1898  enum ObjectKind {
1899  kNormalObject,
1900  kConstantPool,
1901  kScriptInfosList,
1902  };
1903 
1904  // If the object hasn't yet been added to the worklist, add it. Subsequent
1905  // calls with the same object have no effect, even if kind is different.
1906  void QueueVisit(Tagged<HeapObject> obj, ObjectKind kind) {
1907  if (visited_.insert(obj).second) {
1908  to_visit_.push(std::make_pair(obj, kind));
1909  }
1910  }
1911 
1912  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc_;
1913 
1914  LocalIsolate* isolate_;
1915  PtrComprCageBase cage_base_;
1916  std::stack<std::pair<Tagged<HeapObject>, ObjectKind>> to_visit_;
1917 
1918  // Objects that are either in to_visit_ or done being visited. It is safe to
1919  // use HeapObject directly here because GC is disallowed while running this
1920  // visitor.
1921  std::unordered_set<Tagged<HeapObject>, Object::Hasher> visited_;
1922 
1923  ObjectKind current_object_kind_ = kNormalObject;
1924 };
1925 
1926 #endif // ENABLE_SLOW_DCHECKS
1927 
1928 } // namespace
1929 
1930 bool BackgroundCompileTask::is_streaming_compilation() const {
1931  return function_literal_id_ == kFunctionLiteralIdTopLevel;
1932 }
1933 
1934 void BackgroundCompileTask::Run() {
1935  base::FlushDenormalsScope flush_denormals_scope(
1936  isolate_for_local_isolate_->flush_denormals());
1937 
1938  DCHECK_NE(ThreadId::Current(), isolate_for_local_isolate_->thread_id());
1939  LocalIsolate isolate(isolate_for_local_isolate_, ThreadKind::kBackground);
1940  UnparkedScope unparked_scope(&isolate);
1941  LocalHandleScope handle_scope(&isolate);
1942 
1943  ReusableUnoptimizedCompileState reusable_state(&isolate);
1944 
1945  Run(&isolate, &reusable_state);
1946 }
1947 
1948 void BackgroundCompileTask::RunOnMainThread(Isolate* isolate) {
1949  LocalHandleScope handle_scope(isolate->main_thread_local_isolate());
1950  ReusableUnoptimizedCompileState reusable_state(isolate);
1951  Run(isolate->main_thread_local_isolate(), &reusable_state);
1952 }
1953 
1954 void BackgroundCompileTask::Run(
1955  LocalIsolate* isolate, ReusableUnoptimizedCompileState* reusable_state) {
1956  TimedHistogramScope timer(
1957  timer_, nullptr,
1958  compilation_details_
1959  ? &compilation_details_->background_time_in_microseconds
1960  : nullptr);
1961 
1962  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
1963  "BackgroundCompileTask::Run");
1964  RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileCompileTask,
1965  RuntimeCallStats::CounterMode::kThreadSpecific);
1966 
1967  bool toplevel_script_compilation = flags_.is_toplevel();
1968 
1969  ParseInfo info(isolate, flags_, &compile_state_, reusable_state,
1970  GetCurrentStackPosition() - stack_size_ * KB);
1971  info.set_character_stream(std::move(character_stream_));
1972  info.SetCompileHintCallbackAndData(compile_hint_callback_,
1973  compile_hint_callback_data_);
1974  if (is_streaming_compilation()) info.set_is_streaming_compilation();
1975 
1976  if (toplevel_script_compilation) {
1977  DCHECK_NULL(persistent_handles_);
1978  DCHECK(input_shared_info_.is_null());
1979 
1980  // We don't have the script source, origin, or details yet, so use default
1981  // values for them. These will be fixed up during the main-thread merge.
1982  Handle<Script> script = info.CreateScript(
1983  isolate, isolate->factory()->empty_string(), kNullMaybeHandle,
1984  ScriptOriginOptions(false, false, false, info.flags().is_module()));
1985  script_ = isolate->heap()->NewPersistentHandle(script);
1986  } else {
1987  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(persistent_handles_);
1988  isolate->heap()->AttachPersistentHandles(std::move(persistent_handles_));
1989  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info =
1990  input_shared_info_.ToHandleChecked();
1991  script_ = isolate->heap()->NewPersistentHandle(
1992  Cast<Script>(shared_info->script()));
1993  info.CheckFlagsForFunctionFromScript(*script_);
1994 
1995  {
1996  SharedStringAccessGuardIfNeeded access_guard(isolate);
1997  info.set_function_name(info.ast_value_factory()->GetString(
1998  shared_info->Name(), access_guard));
1999  }
2000 
2001  // Get preparsed scope data from the function literal.
2002  if (shared_info->HasUncompiledDataWithPreparseData(isolate)) {
2003  info.set_consumed_preparse_data(ConsumedPreparseData::For(
2004  isolate,
2005  handle(shared_info->uncompiled_data_with_preparse_data(isolate)
2006  ->preparse_data(isolate),
2007  isolate)));
2008  }
2009  }
2010 
2011  // Update the character stream's runtime call stats.
2012  info.character_stream()->set_runtime_call_stats(info.runtime_call_stats());
2013 
2014  Parser parser(isolate, &info);
2015  if (flags().is_toplevel()) {
2016  parser.InitializeEmptyScopeChain(&info);
2017  } else {
2018  // TODO(leszeks): Consider keeping Scope zones alive between compile tasks
2019  // and passing the Scope for the FunctionLiteral through here directly
2020  // without copying/deserializing.
2021  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info =
2022  input_shared_info_.ToHandleChecked();
2023  MaybeDirectHandle<ScopeInfo> maybe_outer_scope_info;
2024  if (shared_info->HasOuterScopeInfo()) {
2025  maybe_outer_scope_info =
2026  direct_handle(shared_info->GetOuterScopeInfo(), isolate);
2027  }
2028  parser.DeserializeScopeChain(
2029  isolate, &info, maybe_outer_scope_info,
2030  Scope::DeserializationMode::kIncludingVariables);
2031  }
2032 
2033  parser.ParseOnBackground(isolate, &info, script_, start_position_,
2034  end_position_, function_literal_id_);
2035  parser.UpdateStatistics(script_, &use_counts_, &total_preparse_skipped_);
2036 
2037  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
2038  "V8.CompileCodeBackground");
2039  RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterIdForCompile(&info),
2040  RuntimeCallStats::CounterMode::kThreadSpecific);
2041 
2042  MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_result;
2043  if (info.literal() != nullptr) {
2044  if (toplevel_script_compilation) {
2045  CreateTopLevelSharedFunctionInfo(&info, script_, isolate);
2046  } else {
2047  // Clone into a placeholder SFI for storing the results.
2048  info.literal()->set_shared_function_info(
2049  isolate->factory()->CloneSharedFunctionInfo(
2050  input_shared_info_.ToHandleChecked()));
2051  }
2052 
2053  if (IterativelyExecuteAndFinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationJobs(
2054  isolate, script_, &info, reusable_state->allocator(),
2055  &is_compiled_scope_, &finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_,
2056  &jobs_to_retry_finalization_on_main_thread_)) {
2057  maybe_result = info.literal()->shared_function_info();
2058  }
2059  }
2060 
2061  if (maybe_result.is_null()) {
2062  PrepareException(isolate, &info);
2063  } else if (v8_flags.enable_slow_asserts) {
2064 #ifdef ENABLE_SLOW_DCHECKS
2065  MergeAssumptionChecker checker(isolate);
2066  checker.IterateObjects(*maybe_result.ToHandleChecked());
2067 #endif
2068  }
2069 
2070  outer_function_sfi_ = isolate->heap()->NewPersistentMaybeHandle(maybe_result);
2071  DCHECK(isolate->heap()->ContainsPersistentHandle(script_.location()));
2072  persistent_handles_ = isolate->heap()->DetachPersistentHandles();
2073 }
2074 
2075 // A class which traverses the constant pools of newly compiled
2076 // SharedFunctionInfos and updates any pointers which need updating.
2077 class ConstantPoolPointerForwarder {
2078  public:
2079  explicit ConstantPoolPointerForwarder(PtrComprCageBase cage_base,
2080  LocalHeap* local_heap,
2081  DirectHandle<Script> old_script)
2082  : cage_base_(cage_base),
2083  local_heap_(local_heap),
2084  old_script_(old_script) {}
2085 
2086  void AddBytecodeArray(Tagged<BytecodeArray> bytecode_array) {
2087  CHECK(IsBytecodeArray(bytecode_array));
2088  bytecode_arrays_to_update_.emplace_back(bytecode_array, local_heap_);
2089  }
2090 
2091  void RecordScopeInfos(Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_old_info) {
2092  RecordScopeInfos(maybe_old_info.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak());
2093  }
2094 
2095  // Record all scope infos relevant for a shared function info or scope info
2096  // (recorded for eval).
2097  void RecordScopeInfos(Tagged<HeapObject> info) {
2098  if (!v8_flags.reuse_scope_infos) return;
2099  Tagged<ScopeInfo> scope_info;
2100  if (Is<SharedFunctionInfo>(info)) {
2101  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> old_sfi = Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(info);
2102  // Also record context-having own scope infos for SFIs.
2103  if (!old_sfi->scope_info()->IsEmpty() &&
2104  old_sfi->scope_info()->HasContext()) {
2105  scope_info = old_sfi->scope_info();
2106  } else if (old_sfi->HasOuterScopeInfo()) {
2107  scope_info = old_sfi->GetOuterScopeInfo();
2108  } else {
2109  return;
2110  }
2111  } else {
2112  scope_info = Cast<ScopeInfo>(info);
2113  }
2114 
2115  while (true) {
2116  auto it = scope_infos_to_update_.find(scope_info->UniqueIdInScript());
2117  if (it != scope_infos_to_update_.end()) {
2118  // Once we find an already recorded scope info, it need to match the one
2119  // on the chain.
2120  if (V8_UNLIKELY(*it->second != scope_info)) {
2121  info->Print();
2122  (*it->second)->Print();
2123  scope_info->Print();
2124  UNREACHABLE();
2125  }
2126  return;
2127  }
2128  scope_infos_to_update_[scope_info->UniqueIdInScript()] =
2129  handle(scope_info, local_heap_);
2130  if (!scope_info->HasOuterScopeInfo()) break;
2131  scope_info = scope_info->OuterScopeInfo();
2132  }
2133  }
2134 
2135  // Runs the update after the setup functions above specified the work to do.
2136  void IterateAndForwardPointers() {
2137  DCHECK(HasAnythingToForward());
2138  for (DirectHandle<BytecodeArray> entry : bytecode_arrays_to_update_) {
2139  local_heap_->Safepoint();
2140  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2141  IterateConstantPool(entry->constant_pool());
2142  }
2143  }
2144 
2145  void set_has_shared_function_info_to_forward() {
2146  has_shared_function_info_to_forward_ = true;
2147  }
2148 
2149  bool HasAnythingToForward() const {
2150  return has_shared_function_info_to_forward_ ||
2151  !scope_infos_to_update_.empty();
2152  }
2153 
2154  // Find an own scope info for the sfi based on the UniqueIdInScript that the
2155  // own scope info would have. This works even if the SFI doesn't yet have a
2156  // scope info attached by computing UniqueIdInScript from the SFI position.
2157  //
2158  // This should only directly be used for SFIs that already existed on the
2159  // script. Their outer scope info will already be correct.
2160  bool InstallOwnScopeInfo(Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi) {
2161  if (!v8_flags.reuse_scope_infos) return false;
2162  auto it = scope_infos_to_update_.find(sfi->UniqueIdInScript());
2163  if (it == scope_infos_to_update_.end()) return false;
2164  sfi->SetScopeInfo(*it->second);
2165  return true;
2166  }
2167 
2168  // Either replace the own scope info of the sfi, or the first outer scope info
2169  // that was recorded.
2170  //
2171  // This has to be used for all newly created SFIs since their outer scope info
2172  // also may need to be reattached.
2173  void UpdateScopeInfo(Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi) {
2174  if (!v8_flags.reuse_scope_infos) return;
2175  if (InstallOwnScopeInfo(sfi)) return;
2176  if (!sfi->HasOuterScopeInfo()) return;
2177 
2178  Tagged<ScopeInfo> parent =
2179  sfi->scope_info()->IsEmpty() ? Tagged<ScopeInfo>() : sfi->scope_info();
2180  Tagged<ScopeInfo> outer_info = sfi->GetOuterScopeInfo();
2181 
2182  auto it = scope_infos_to_update_.find(outer_info->UniqueIdInScript());
2183  while (it == scope_infos_to_update_.end()) {
2184  if (!outer_info->HasOuterScopeInfo()) return;
2185  parent = outer_info;
2186  outer_info = outer_info->OuterScopeInfo();
2187  it = scope_infos_to_update_.find(outer_info->UniqueIdInScript());
2188  }
2189  if (outer_info == *it->second) return;
2190 
2191  VerifyScopeInfo(outer_info, *it->second);
2192 
2193  if (parent.is_null()) {
2194  sfi->set_raw_outer_scope_info_or_feedback_metadata(*it->second);
2195  } else {
2196  parent->set_outer_scope_info(*it->second);
2197  }
2198  }
2199 
2200  private:
2201  void VerifyScopeInfo(Tagged<ScopeInfo> scope_info,
2202  Tagged<ScopeInfo> replacement) {
2203  if (replacement->scope_type() == SCRIPT_SCOPE ||
2204  replacement->scope_type() == MODULE_SCOPE) {
2205  // During streaming compilation we might not know whether we want to parse
2206  // this script as a classic script or module, and do the wrong thing. In
2207  // case compilation succeeded, we'll only reject the result later.
2208  CHECK(scope_info->scope_type() == SCRIPT_SCOPE ||
2209  scope_info->scope_type() == MODULE_SCOPE);
2210  } else {
2211  CHECK_EQ(replacement->EndPosition(), scope_info->EndPosition());
2212  CHECK_EQ(replacement->scope_type(), scope_info->scope_type());
2213  CHECK_EQ(replacement->ContextLength(), scope_info->ContextLength());
2214  }
2215  }
2216  template <typename TArray>
2217  void IterateConstantPoolEntry(Tagged<TArray> constant_pool, int i) {
2218  Tagged<Object> obj = constant_pool->get(i);
2219  if (IsSmi(obj)) return;
2220  Tagged<HeapObject> heap_obj = Cast<HeapObject>(obj);
2221  if (IsFixedArray(heap_obj, cage_base_)) {
2222  // Constant pools can have nested fixed arrays, but such relationships
2223  // are acyclic and never more than a few layers deep, so recursion is
2224  // fine here.
2225  IterateConstantPoolNestedArray(Cast<FixedArray>(heap_obj));
2226  } else if (has_shared_function_info_to_forward_ &&
2227  IsSharedFunctionInfo(heap_obj, cage_base_)) {
2228  VisitSharedFunctionInfo(constant_pool, i,
2229  Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(heap_obj));
2230  } else if (!scope_infos_to_update_.empty() &&
2231  IsScopeInfo(heap_obj, cage_base_)) {
2232  VisitScopeInfo(constant_pool, i, Cast<ScopeInfo>(heap_obj));
2233  }
2234  }
2235 
2236  template <typename TArray>
2237  void VisitSharedFunctionInfo(Tagged<TArray> constant_pool, int i,
2238  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi) {
2239  Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_old_sfi =
2240  old_script_->infos()->get(sfi->function_literal_id(kRelaxedLoad));
2241  if (maybe_old_sfi.IsWeak()) {
2242  constant_pool->set(
2243  i, Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(maybe_old_sfi.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak()));
2244  }
2245  }
2246 
2247  template <typename TArray>
2248  void VisitScopeInfo(Tagged<TArray> constant_pool, int i,
2249  Tagged<ScopeInfo> scope_info) {
2250  auto it = scope_infos_to_update_.find(scope_info->UniqueIdInScript());
2251  // Try to replace the scope info itself with an already existing version.
2252  if (it != scope_infos_to_update_.end()) {
2253  if (scope_info != *it->second) {
2254  VerifyScopeInfo(scope_info, *it->second);
2255  constant_pool->set(i, *it->second);
2256  }
2257  } else if (scope_info->HasOuterScopeInfo()) {
2258  // If we didn't find a match, but we have an outer scope info, try to
2259  // replace the outer scope info with an already existing outer scope
2260  // info. We only need to look at the direct outer scope info since we'll
2261  // process all scope infos that are created by this compilation task.
2262  Tagged<ScopeInfo> outer = scope_info->OuterScopeInfo();
2263  it = scope_infos_to_update_.find(outer->UniqueIdInScript());
2264  if (it != scope_infos_to_update_.end() && outer != *it->second) {
2265  VerifyScopeInfo(outer, *it->second);
2266  scope_info->set_outer_scope_info(*it->second);
2267  }
2268  }
2269  }
2270 
2271  void IterateConstantPool(Tagged<TrustedFixedArray> constant_pool) {
2272  for (int i = 0, length = constant_pool->length(); i < length; ++i) {
2273  IterateConstantPoolEntry(constant_pool, i);
2274  }
2275  }
2276 
2277  void IterateConstantPoolNestedArray(Tagged<FixedArray> nested_array) {
2278  for (int i = 0, length = nested_array->length(); i < length; ++i) {
2279  IterateConstantPoolEntry(nested_array, i);
2280  }
2281  }
2282 
2283  PtrComprCageBase cage_base_;
2284  LocalHeap* local_heap_;
2285  DirectHandle<Script> old_script_;
2286  std::vector<IndirectHandle<BytecodeArray>> bytecode_arrays_to_update_;
2287 
2288  // Indicates whether we have any shared function info to forward.
2289  bool has_shared_function_info_to_forward_ = false;
2290  std::unordered_map<int, IndirectHandle<ScopeInfo>> scope_infos_to_update_;
2291 };
2292 
2293 void BackgroundMergeTask::SetUpOnMainThread(Isolate* isolate,
2294  Handle<String> source_text,
2295  const ScriptDetails& script_details,
2296  LanguageMode language_mode) {
2297  DCHECK_EQ(state_, kNotStarted);
2298 
2299  HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
2300 
2301  CompilationCacheScript::LookupResult lookup_result =
2302  isolate->compilation_cache()->LookupScript(source_text, script_details,
2303  language_mode);
2304  DirectHandle<Script> script;
2305  if (!lookup_result.script().ToHandle(&script)) {
2306  state_ = kDone;
2307  return;
2308  }
2309 
2310  if (lookup_result.is_compiled_scope().is_compiled()) {
2311  // There already exists a compiled top-level SFI, so the main thread will
2312  // discard the background serialization results and use the top-level SFI
2313  // from the cache, assuming the top-level SFI is still compiled by then.
2314  // Thus, there is no need to keep the Script pointer for background merging.
2315  // Do nothing in this case.
2316  state_ = kDone;
2317  } else {
2318  DCHECK(lookup_result.toplevel_sfi().is_null());
2319  // A background merge is required.
2320  SetUpOnMainThread(isolate, script);
2321  }
2322 }
2323 
2324 namespace {
2325 void VerifyCodeMerge(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Script> script) {
2326  if (!v8_flags.reuse_scope_infos) return;
2327  // Check that:
2328  // * There aren't any duplicate scope info. Every scope/context should
2329  // correspond to at most one scope info.
2330  // * All published SFIs refer to the old script (i.e. we chose new vs old
2331  // correctly, and updated new SFIs where needed).
2332  // * All constant pool SFI entries point to an SFI referring to the old
2333  // script (i.e. references were updated correctly).
2334  std::unordered_map<int, Tagged<ScopeInfo>> scope_infos;
2335  for (int info_idx = 0; info_idx < script->infos()->length(); info_idx++) {
2336  Tagged<ScopeInfo> scope_info;
2337  if (!script->infos()->get(info_idx).IsWeak()) continue;
2338  Tagged<HeapObject> info =
2339  script->infos()->get(info_idx).GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak();
2340  if (Is<SharedFunctionInfo>(info)) {
2341  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi = Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(info);
2342  CHECK_EQ(sfi->script(), *script);
2343 
2344  if (sfi->HasBytecodeArray()) {
2345  Tagged<BytecodeArray> bytecode = sfi->GetBytecodeArray(isolate);
2346  Tagged<TrustedFixedArray> constant_pool = bytecode->constant_pool();
2347  for (int constant_idx = 0; constant_idx < constant_pool->length();
2348  ++constant_idx) {
2349  Tagged<Object> entry = constant_pool->get(constant_idx);
2350  if (Is<SharedFunctionInfo>(entry)) {
2351  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> inner_sfi =
2352  Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(entry);
2353  int id = inner_sfi->function_literal_id(kRelaxedLoad);
2354  CHECK_EQ(MakeWeak(inner_sfi), script->infos()->get(id));
2355  CHECK_EQ(inner_sfi->script(), *script);
2356  }
2357  }
2358  }
2359 
2360  if (!sfi->scope_info()->IsEmpty()) {
2361  scope_info = sfi->scope_info();
2362  } else if (sfi->HasOuterScopeInfo()) {
2363  scope_info = sfi->GetOuterScopeInfo();
2364  } else {
2365  continue;
2366  }
2367  } else {
2368  scope_info = Cast<ScopeInfo>(info);
2369  }
2370  while (true) {
2371  auto it = scope_infos.find(scope_info->UniqueIdInScript());
2372  if (it != scope_infos.end()) {
2373  if (*it->second != scope_info) {
2374  isolate->PushParamsAndDie(reinterpret_cast<void*>(it->second->ptr()),
2375  reinterpret_cast<void*>(scope_info.ptr()));
2376  UNREACHABLE();
2377  }
2378  break;
2379  }
2380  scope_infos[scope_info->UniqueIdInScript()] = scope_info;
2381  if (!scope_info->HasOuterScopeInfo()) break;
2382  scope_info = scope_info->OuterScopeInfo();
2383  }
2384  }
2385 }
2386 } // namespace
2387 
2388 void BackgroundMergeTask::SetUpOnMainThread(
2389  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Script> cached_script) {
2390  // Any data sent to the background thread will need to be a persistent handle.
2391 #ifdef DEBUG
2392  VerifyCodeMerge(isolate, cached_script);
2393 #else
2394  if (v8_flags.verify_code_merge) {
2395  VerifyCodeMerge(isolate, cached_script);
2396  }
2397 #endif
2398 
2399  persistent_handles_ = std::make_unique<PersistentHandles>(isolate);
2400  state_ = kPendingBackgroundWork;
2401  cached_script_ = persistent_handles_->NewHandle(*cached_script);
2402 }
2403 
2404 static bool force_gc_during_next_merge_for_testing_ = false;
2405 
2406 void BackgroundMergeTask::ForceGCDuringNextMergeForTesting() {
2407  force_gc_during_next_merge_for_testing_ = true;
2408 }
2409 
2410 void BackgroundMergeTask::BeginMergeInBackground(
2411  LocalIsolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Script> new_script) {
2412  DCHECK_EQ(state_, kPendingBackgroundWork);
2413 
2414  LocalHeap* local_heap = isolate->heap();
2415  local_heap->AttachPersistentHandles(std::move(persistent_handles_));
2416  LocalHandleScope handle_scope(local_heap);
2417  DirectHandle<Script> old_script = cached_script_.ToHandleChecked();
2418  ConstantPoolPointerForwarder forwarder(isolate, local_heap, old_script);
2419 
2420  {
2421  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2422  Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_old_toplevel_sfi =
2423  old_script->infos()->get(kFunctionLiteralIdTopLevel);
2424  if (maybe_old_toplevel_sfi.IsWeak()) {
2425  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> old_toplevel_sfi = Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(
2426  maybe_old_toplevel_sfi.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak());
2427  toplevel_sfi_from_cached_script_ =
2428  local_heap->NewPersistentHandle(old_toplevel_sfi);
2429  }
2430  }
2431 
2432  // Iterate the SFI lists on both Scripts to set up the forwarding table and
2433  // follow-up worklists for the main thread.
2434  CHECK_EQ(old_script->infos()->length(), new_script->infos()->length());
2435  for (int i = 0; i < old_script->infos()->length(); ++i) {
2436  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2437  Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_new_sfi = new_script->infos()->get(i);
2438  Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_old_info = old_script->infos()->get(i);
2439  // We might have scope infos in the table if it's deserialized from a code
2440  // cache.
2441  if (maybe_new_sfi.IsWeak() &&
2442  Is<SharedFunctionInfo>(maybe_new_sfi.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak())) {
2443  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> new_sfi =
2444  Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(maybe_new_sfi.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak());
2445  if (maybe_old_info.IsWeak()) {
2446  forwarder.set_has_shared_function_info_to_forward();
2447  // The old script and the new script both have SharedFunctionInfos for
2448  // this function literal.
2449  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> old_sfi =
2450  Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(maybe_old_info.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak());
2451  // Make sure to allocate a persistent handle to the old sfi whether or
2452  // not it or the new sfi have bytecode -- this is necessary to keep the
2453  // old sfi reference in the old script list alive, so that pointers to
2454  // the new sfi are redirected to the old sfi.
2455  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> old_sfi_handle =
2456  local_heap->NewPersistentHandle(old_sfi);
2457  if (old_sfi->HasBytecodeArray()) {
2458  // Reset the old SFI's bytecode age so that it won't likely get
2459  // flushed right away. This operation might be racing against
2460  // concurrent modification by another thread, but such a race is not
2461  // catastrophic.
2462  old_sfi->set_age(0);
2463  } else if (new_sfi->HasBytecodeArray()) {
2464  // Also push the old_sfi to make sure it stays alive / isn't replaced.
2465  new_compiled_data_for_cached_sfis_.push_back(
2466  {old_sfi_handle, local_heap->NewPersistentHandle(new_sfi)});
2467  Tagged<ScopeInfo> info = old_sfi->scope_info();
2468  if (!info->IsEmpty()) {
2469  new_sfi->SetScopeInfo(info);
2470  } else if (old_sfi->HasOuterScopeInfo()) {
2471  new_sfi->scope_info()->set_outer_scope_info(
2472  old_sfi->GetOuterScopeInfo());
2473  }
2474  forwarder.AddBytecodeArray(new_sfi->GetBytecodeArray(isolate));
2475  }
2476  } else {
2477  // The old script didn't have a SharedFunctionInfo for this function
2478  // literal, so it can use the new SharedFunctionInfo.
2479  new_sfi->set_script(*old_script, kReleaseStore);
2480  used_new_sfis_.push_back(local_heap->NewPersistentHandle(new_sfi));
2481  if (new_sfi->HasBytecodeArray()) {
2482  forwarder.AddBytecodeArray(new_sfi->GetBytecodeArray(isolate));
2483  }
2484  }
2485  }
2486 
2487  if (maybe_old_info.IsWeak()) {
2488  forwarder.RecordScopeInfos(maybe_old_info);
2489  // If the old script has a SFI, point to it from the new script to
2490  // indicate we've already seen it and we'll reuse it if necessary (if
2491  // newly compiled bytecode points to it).
2492  new_script->infos()->set(i, maybe_old_info);
2493  }
2494  }
2495 
2496  // Since we are walking the script infos weak list both when figuring out
2497  // which SFIs to merge above, and actually merging them below, make sure that
2498  // a GC here which clears any dead weak refs or flushes any bytecode doesn't
2499  // break anything.
2500  if (V8_UNLIKELY(force_gc_during_next_merge_for_testing_)) {
2501  // This GC is only synchronous on the main thread at the moment.
2502  DCHECK(isolate->is_main_thread());
2503  local_heap->AsHeap()->CollectAllAvailableGarbage(
2504  GarbageCollectionReason::kTesting);
2505  }
2506 
2507  if (forwarder.HasAnythingToForward()) {
2508  for (DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> new_sfi : used_new_sfis_) {
2509  forwarder.UpdateScopeInfo(*new_sfi);
2510  }
2511  for (const auto& new_compiled_data : new_compiled_data_for_cached_sfis_) {
2512  // It's possible that new_compiled_data.cached_sfi had
2513  // scope_info()->IsEmpty() while an inner function has scope info if the
2514  // cached_sfi was recreated when an outer function was recompiled. If so,
2515  // new_compiled_data.new_sfi does not have a reused scope info yet, and
2516  // we'll have found it when we visited the inner function. Try to pick it
2517  // up here.
2518  forwarder.InstallOwnScopeInfo(*new_compiled_data.new_sfi);
2519  }
2520  forwarder.IterateAndForwardPointers();
2521  }
2522  persistent_handles_ = local_heap->DetachPersistentHandles();
2523  state_ = kPendingForegroundWork;
2524 }
2525 
2526 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> BackgroundMergeTask::CompleteMergeInForeground(
2527  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Script> new_script) {
2528  DCHECK_EQ(state_, kPendingForegroundWork);
2529 
2530  HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
2531  DirectHandle<Script> old_script = cached_script_.ToHandleChecked();
2532  ConstantPoolPointerForwarder forwarder(
2533  isolate, isolate->main_thread_local_heap(), old_script);
2534 
2535  for (const auto& new_compiled_data : new_compiled_data_for_cached_sfis_) {
2536  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi = *new_compiled_data.cached_sfi;
2537  if (!sfi->is_compiled() && new_compiled_data.new_sfi->is_compiled()) {
2538  // Updating existing DebugInfos is not supported, but we don't expect
2539  // uncompiled SharedFunctionInfos to contain DebugInfos.
2540  DCHECK(!new_compiled_data.cached_sfi->HasDebugInfo(isolate));
2541  // The goal here is to copy every field except script from
2542  // new_sfi to cached_sfi. The safest way to do so (including a DCHECK that
2543  // no fields were skipped) is to first copy the script from
2544  // cached_sfi to new_sfi, and then copy every field using CopyFrom.
2545  new_compiled_data.new_sfi->set_script(sfi->script(kAcquireLoad),
2546  kReleaseStore);
2547  sfi->CopyFrom(*new_compiled_data.new_sfi, isolate);
2548  }
2549  }
2550 
2551  for (int i = 0; i < old_script->infos()->length(); ++i) {
2552  Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_old_info = old_script->infos()->get(i);
2553  Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_new_info = new_script->infos()->get(i);
2554  if (maybe_new_info == maybe_old_info) continue;
2555  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2556  if (maybe_old_info.IsWeak()) {
2557  // The old script's SFI didn't exist during the background work, but does
2558  // now. This means a re-merge is necessary. Potential references to the
2559  // new script's SFI need to be updated to point to the cached script's SFI
2560  // instead. The cached script's SFI's outer scope infos need to be used by
2561  // the new script's outer SFIs.
2562  if (Is<SharedFunctionInfo>(maybe_old_info.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak())) {
2563  forwarder.set_has_shared_function_info_to_forward();
2564  }
2565  forwarder.RecordScopeInfos(maybe_old_info);
2566  } else {
2567  old_script->infos()->set(i, maybe_new_info);
2568  }
2569  }
2570 
2571  // Most of the time, the background merge was sufficient. However, if there
2572  // are any new pointers that need forwarding, a new traversal of the constant
2573  // pools is required.
2574  if (forwarder.HasAnythingToForward()) {
2575  for (DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> new_sfi : used_new_sfis_) {
2576  forwarder.UpdateScopeInfo(*new_sfi);
2577  if (new_sfi->HasBytecodeArray(isolate)) {
2578  forwarder.AddBytecodeArray(new_sfi->GetBytecodeArray(isolate));
2579  }
2580  }
2581  for (const auto& new_compiled_data : new_compiled_data_for_cached_sfis_) {
2582  // It's possible that cached_sfi wasn't compiled, but an inner function
2583  // existed that didn't exist when be background merged. In that case, pick
2584  // up the relevant scope infos.
2585  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi = *new_compiled_data.cached_sfi;
2586  forwarder.InstallOwnScopeInfo(sfi);
2587  if (new_compiled_data.cached_sfi->HasBytecodeArray(isolate)) {
2588  forwarder.AddBytecodeArray(
2589  new_compiled_data.cached_sfi->GetBytecodeArray(isolate));
2590  }
2591  }
2592  forwarder.IterateAndForwardPointers();
2593  }
2594 
2595  Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_toplevel_sfi =
2596  old_script->infos()->get(kFunctionLiteralIdTopLevel);
2597  CHECK(maybe_toplevel_sfi.IsWeak());
2598  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> result = handle(
2599  Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(maybe_toplevel_sfi.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak()),
2600  isolate);
2601 
2602  state_ = kDone;
2603 
2604  if (isolate->NeedsSourcePositions()) {
2605  Script::InitLineEnds(isolate, new_script);
2606  SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(isolate, result);
2607  }
2608 
2609 #ifdef DEBUG
2610  VerifyCodeMerge(isolate, old_script);
2611 #else
2612  if (v8_flags.verify_code_merge) {
2613  VerifyCodeMerge(isolate, old_script);
2614  }
2615 #endif
2616 
2617  return handle_scope.CloseAndEscape(result);
2618 }
2619 
2620 MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> BackgroundCompileTask::FinalizeScript(
2621  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> source,
2622  const ScriptDetails& script_details,
2623  MaybeDirectHandle<Script> maybe_cached_script) {
2624  ScriptOriginOptions origin_options = script_details.origin_options;
2625 
2626  DCHECK(flags_.is_toplevel());
2627  DCHECK_EQ(flags_.is_module(), origin_options.IsModule());
2628 
2629  MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_result;
2630  Handle<Script> script = script_;
2631 
2632  // We might not have been able to finalize all jobs on the background
2633  // thread (e.g. asm.js jobs), so finalize those deferred jobs now.
2634  if (FinalizeDeferredUnoptimizedCompilationJobs(
2635  isolate, script, &jobs_to_retry_finalization_on_main_thread_,
2636  compile_state_.pending_error_handler(),
2637  &finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_)) {
2638  maybe_result = outer_function_sfi_;
2639  }
2640 
2641  if (DirectHandle<Script> cached_script;
2642  maybe_cached_script.ToHandle(&cached_script) && !maybe_result.is_null()) {
2643  BackgroundMergeTask merge;
2644  merge.SetUpOnMainThread(isolate, cached_script);
2645  CHECK(merge.HasPendingBackgroundWork());
2646  merge.BeginMergeInBackground(isolate->AsLocalIsolate(), script);
2647  CHECK(merge.HasPendingForegroundWork());
2648  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result =
2649  merge.CompleteMergeInForeground(isolate, script);
2650  maybe_result = result;
2651  script = handle(Cast<Script>(result->script()), isolate);
2652  DCHECK(Object::StrictEquals(script->source(), *source));
2653  DCHECK(isolate->factory()->script_list()->Contains(MakeWeak(*script)));
2654  } else {
2655  Script::SetSource(isolate, script, source);
2656  script->set_origin_options(origin_options);
2657 
2658  // The one post-hoc fix-up: Add the script to the script list.
2659  DirectHandle<WeakArrayList> scripts = isolate->factory()->script_list();
2660  scripts = WeakArrayList::Append(isolate, scripts,
2661  MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(script));
2662  isolate->heap()->SetRootScriptList(*scripts);
2663 
2664  // Set the script fields after finalization, to keep this path the same
2665  // between main-thread and off-thread finalization.
2666  {
2667  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2668  SetScriptFieldsFromDetails(isolate, *script, script_details, &no_gc);
2669  LOG(isolate, ScriptDetails(*script));
2670  }
2671  }
2672 
2673  ReportStatistics(isolate);
2674 
2675  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result;
2676  if (!maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
2677  FailWithPreparedException(isolate, script,
2678  compile_state_.pending_error_handler());
2679  return kNullMaybeHandle;
2680  }
2681 
2682  FinalizeUnoptimizedScriptCompilation(isolate, script, flags_, &compile_state_,
2683  finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_);
2684 
2685  return handle(*result, isolate);
2686 }
2687 
2688 bool BackgroundCompileTask::FinalizeFunction(
2689  Isolate* isolate, Compiler::ClearExceptionFlag flag) {
2690  DCHECK(!flags_.is_toplevel());
2691 
2692  MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_result;
2693  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> input_shared_info =
2694  input_shared_info_.ToHandleChecked();
2695 
2696  // The UncompiledData on the input SharedFunctionInfo will have a pointer to
2697  // the LazyCompileDispatcher Job that launched this task, which will now be
2698  // considered complete, so clear that regardless of whether the finalize
2699  // succeeds or not.
2700  input_shared_info->ClearUncompiledDataJobPointer(isolate);
2701 
2702  // We might not have been able to finalize all jobs on the background
2703  // thread (e.g. asm.js jobs), so finalize those deferred jobs now.
2704  if (FinalizeDeferredUnoptimizedCompilationJobs(
2705  isolate, script_, &jobs_to_retry_finalization_on_main_thread_,
2706  compile_state_.pending_error_handler(),
2707  &finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_)) {
2708  maybe_result = outer_function_sfi_;
2709  }
2710 
2711  ReportStatistics(isolate);
2712 
2713  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result;
2714  if (!maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
2715  FailWithPreparedException(isolate, script_,
2716  compile_state_.pending_error_handler(), flag);
2717  return false;
2718  }
2719 
2720  FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilation(isolate, script_, flags_, &compile_state_,
2721  finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_);
2722 
2723  // Move the compiled data from the placeholder SFI back to the real SFI.
2724  input_shared_info->CopyFrom(*result, isolate);
2725 
2726  return true;
2727 }
2728 
2729 void BackgroundCompileTask::AbortFunction() {
2730  // The UncompiledData on the input SharedFunctionInfo will have a pointer to
2731  // the LazyCompileDispatcher Job that launched this task, which is about to be
2732  // deleted, so clear that to avoid the SharedFunctionInfo from pointing to
2733  // deallocated memory.
2734  input_shared_info_.ToHandleChecked()->ClearUncompiledDataJobPointer(
2735  isolate_for_local_isolate_);
2736 }
2737 
2738 void BackgroundCompileTask::ReportStatistics(Isolate* isolate) {
2739  // Update use-counts.
2740  for (auto feature : use_counts_) {
2741  isolate->CountUsage(feature);
2742  }
2743 }
2744 
2745 BackgroundDeserializeTask::BackgroundDeserializeTask(
2746  Isolate* isolate, std::unique_ptr<ScriptCompiler::CachedData> cached_data)
2747  : isolate_for_local_isolate_(isolate),
2748  cached_data_(cached_data->data, cached_data->length),
2749  timer_(isolate->counters()->deserialize_script_on_background()) {
2750  // If the passed in cached data has ownership of the buffer, move it to the
2751  // task.
2752  if (cached_data->buffer_policy == ScriptCompiler::CachedData::BufferOwned &&
2753  !cached_data_.HasDataOwnership()) {
2754  cached_data->buffer_policy = ScriptCompiler::CachedData::BufferNotOwned;
2755  cached_data_.AcquireDataOwnership();
2756  }
2757 }
2758 
2759 void BackgroundDeserializeTask::Run() {
2760  TimedHistogramScope timer(timer_, nullptr, &background_time_in_microseconds_);
2761  LocalIsolate isolate(isolate_for_local_isolate_, ThreadKind::kBackground);
2762  UnparkedScope unparked_scope(&isolate);
2763  LocalHandleScope handle_scope(&isolate);
2764 
2765  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> inner_result;
2766  off_thread_data_ =
2767  CodeSerializer::StartDeserializeOffThread(&isolate, &cached_data_);
2768  if (v8_flags.enable_slow_asserts && off_thread_data_.HasResult()) {
2769 #ifdef ENABLE_SLOW_DCHECKS
2770  MergeAssumptionChecker checker(&isolate);
2771  checker.IterateObjects(*off_thread_data_.GetOnlyScript(isolate.heap()));
2772 #endif
2773  }
2774 }

2781  background_merge_task_.SetUpOnMainThread(isolate, source_text, script_details,
2782  language_mode);
2783 }

2810 // ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2811 // Implementation of Compiler
2812 
2813 // static
2814 bool Compiler::CollectSourcePositions(
2815  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info) {
2816  DCHECK(shared_info->is_compiled());
2817  DCHECK(shared_info->HasBytecodeArray());
2818  DCHECK(!shared_info->GetBytecodeArray(isolate)->HasSourcePositionTable());
2819 
2820  // Source position collection should be context independent.
2821  NullContextScope null_context_scope(isolate);
2822 
2823  // Collecting source positions requires allocating a new source position
2824  // table.
2825  DCHECK(AllowHeapAllocation::IsAllowed());
2826 
2827  Handle<BytecodeArray> bytecode =
2828  handle(shared_info->GetBytecodeArray(isolate), isolate);
2829 
2830  // TODO(v8:8510): Push the CLEAR_EXCEPTION flag or something like it down into
2831  // the parser so it aborts without setting an exception, which then
2832  // gets thrown. This would avoid the situation where potentially we'd reparse
2833  // several times (running out of stack each time) before hitting this limit.
2834  if (GetCurrentStackPosition() < isolate->stack_guard()->real_climit()) {
2835  // Stack is already exhausted.
2836  bytecode->SetSourcePositionsFailedToCollect();
2837  return false;
2838  }
2839 
2840  // Unfinalized scripts don't yet have the proper source string attached and
2841  // thus can't be reparsed.
2842  if (Cast<Script>(shared_info->script())->IsMaybeUnfinalized(isolate)) {
2843  bytecode->SetSourcePositionsFailedToCollect();
2844  return false;
2845  }
2846 
2847  DCHECK(AllowCompilation::IsAllowed(isolate));
2848  DCHECK_EQ(ThreadId::Current(), isolate->thread_id());
2849 
2850  DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
2851  VMState<BYTECODE_COMPILER> state(isolate);
2852  PostponeInterruptsScope postpone(isolate);
2853  RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileCollectSourcePositions);
2854  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
2855  "V8.CollectSourcePositions");
2856  NestedTimedHistogramScope timer(
2857  isolate->counters()->collect_source_positions());
2858 
2859  // Set up parse info.
2860  UnoptimizedCompileFlags flags =
2861  UnoptimizedCompileFlags::ForFunctionCompile(isolate, *shared_info);
2862  flags.set_collect_source_positions(true);
2863  flags.set_is_reparse(true);
2864  // Prevent parallel tasks from being spawned by this job.
2865  flags.set_post_parallel_compile_tasks_for_eager_toplevel(false);
2866  flags.set_post_parallel_compile_tasks_for_lazy(false);
2867 
2868  UnoptimizedCompileState compile_state;
2869  ReusableUnoptimizedCompileState reusable_state(isolate);
2870  ParseInfo parse_info(isolate, flags, &compile_state, &reusable_state);
2871 
2872  // Parse and update ParseInfo with the results. Don't update parsing
2873  // statistics since we've already parsed the code before.
2874  if (!parsing::ParseAny(&parse_info, shared_info, isolate,
2875  parsing::ReportStatisticsMode::kNo)) {
2876  // Parsing failed probably as a result of stack exhaustion.
2877  bytecode->SetSourcePositionsFailedToCollect();
2878  return FailAndClearException(isolate);
2879  }
2880 
2881  // Character stream shouldn't be used again.
2882  parse_info.ResetCharacterStream();
2883 
2884  // Generate the unoptimized bytecode.
2885  // TODO(v8:8510): Consider forcing preparsing of inner functions to avoid
2886  // wasting time fully parsing them when they won't ever be used.
2887  std::unique_ptr<UnoptimizedCompilationJob> job;
2888  {
2889  job = interpreter::Interpreter::NewSourcePositionCollectionJob(
2890  &parse_info, parse_info.literal(), bytecode, isolate->allocator(),
2891  isolate->main_thread_local_isolate());
2892 
2893  if (!job || job->ExecuteJob() != CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED ||
2894  job->FinalizeJob(shared_info, isolate) != CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED) {
2895  // Recompiling failed probably as a result of stack exhaustion.
2896  bytecode->SetSourcePositionsFailedToCollect();
2897  return FailAndClearException(isolate);
2898  }
2899  }
2900 
2901  DCHECK(job->compilation_info()->flags().collect_source_positions());
2902 
2903  // If debugging, make sure that instrumented bytecode has the source position
2904  // table set on it as well.
2905  if (std::optional<Tagged<DebugInfo>> debug_info =
2906  shared_info->TryGetDebugInfo(isolate)) {
2907  if (debug_info.value()->HasInstrumentedBytecodeArray()) {
2908  Tagged<TrustedByteArray> source_position_table =
2909  job->compilation_info()->bytecode_array()->SourcePositionTable();
2910  shared_info->GetActiveBytecodeArray(isolate)->set_source_position_table(
2911  source_position_table, kReleaseStore);
2912  }
2913  }
2914 
2915  DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
2916  DCHECK(shared_info->is_compiled_scope(isolate).is_compiled());
2917  return true;
2918 }
2919 
2920 // static
2921 bool Compiler::Compile(Isolate* isolate, Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info,
2922  ClearExceptionFlag flag,
2923  IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope,
2924  CreateSourcePositions create_source_positions_flag) {
2925  // We should never reach here if the function is already compiled.
2926  DCHECK(!shared_info->is_compiled());
2927  DCHECK(!is_compiled_scope->is_compiled());
2928  DCHECK(AllowCompilation::IsAllowed(isolate));
2929  DCHECK_EQ(ThreadId::Current(), isolate->thread_id());
2930  DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
2931  DCHECK(!shared_info->HasBytecodeArray());
2932 
2933  VMState<BYTECODE_COMPILER> state(isolate);
2934  PostponeInterruptsScope postpone(isolate);
2935  TimerEventScope<TimerEventCompileCode> compile_timer(isolate);
2936  RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileFunction);
2937  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"), "V8.CompileCode");
2938  AggregatedHistogramTimerScope timer(isolate->counters()->compile_lazy());
2939 
2940  Handle<Script> script(Cast<Script>(shared_info->script()), isolate);
2941 
2942  // Set up parse info.
2943  UnoptimizedCompileFlags flags =
2944  UnoptimizedCompileFlags::ForFunctionCompile(isolate, *shared_info);
2945  if (create_source_positions_flag == CreateSourcePositions::kYes) {
2946  flags.set_collect_source_positions(true);
2947  }
2948 
2949  UnoptimizedCompileState compile_state;
2950  ReusableUnoptimizedCompileState reusable_state(isolate);
2951  ParseInfo parse_info(isolate, flags, &compile_state, &reusable_state);
2952 
2953  // Check if the compiler dispatcher has shared_info enqueued for compile.
2954  LazyCompileDispatcher* dispatcher = isolate->lazy_compile_dispatcher();
2955  if (dispatcher && dispatcher->IsEnqueued(shared_info)) {
2956  if (!dispatcher->FinishNow(shared_info)) {
2957  return FailWithException(isolate, script, &parse_info, flag);
2958  }
2959  *is_compiled_scope = shared_info->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
2960  DCHECK(is_compiled_scope->is_compiled());
2961  return true;
2962  }
2963 
2964  if (shared_info->HasUncompiledDataWithPreparseData(isolate)) {
2965  parse_info.set_consumed_preparse_data(ConsumedPreparseData::For(
2966  isolate, handle(shared_info->uncompiled_data_with_preparse_data(isolate)
2967  ->preparse_data(),
2968  isolate)));
2969  }
2970 
2971  // Parse and update ParseInfo with the results.
2972  if (!parsing::ParseAny(&parse_info, shared_info, isolate,
2973  parsing::ReportStatisticsMode::kYes)) {
2974  return FailWithException(isolate, script, &parse_info, flag);
2975  }
2976  parse_info.literal()->set_shared_function_info(shared_info);
2977 
2978  // Generate the unoptimized bytecode or asm-js data.
2979  FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationDataList
2980  finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list;
2981 
2982  if (!IterativelyExecuteAndFinalizeUnoptimizedCompilationJobs(
2983  isolate, script, &parse_info, isolate->allocator(), is_compiled_scope,
2984  &finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list, nullptr)) {
2985  return FailWithException(isolate, script, &parse_info, flag);
2986  }
2987 
2988  FinalizeUnoptimizedCompilation(isolate, script, flags, &compile_state,
2989  finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list);
2990 
2991  if (v8_flags.always_sparkplug) {
2992  CompileAllWithBaseline(isolate, finalize_unoptimized_compilation_data_list);
2993  }
2994 
2995  if (script->produce_compile_hints()) {
2996  // Log lazy function compilation.
2997  DirectHandle<ArrayList> list;
2998  if (IsUndefined(script->compiled_lazy_function_positions())) {
2999  constexpr int kInitialLazyFunctionPositionListSize = 100;
3000  list = ArrayList::New(isolate, kInitialLazyFunctionPositionListSize);
3001  } else {
3002  list = direct_handle(
3003  Cast<ArrayList>(script->compiled_lazy_function_positions()), isolate);
3004  }
3005  list = ArrayList::Add(isolate, list,
3006  Smi::FromInt(shared_info->StartPosition()));
3007  script->set_compiled_lazy_function_positions(*list);
3008  }
3009 
3010  DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
3011  DCHECK(is_compiled_scope->is_compiled());
3012  return true;
3013 }
3014 
3015 // static
3016 bool Compiler::Compile(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
3017  ClearExceptionFlag flag,
3018  IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope) {
3019  // We should never reach here if the function is already compiled or
3020  // optimized.
3021  DCHECK(!function->is_compiled(isolate));
3022  DCHECK_IMPLIES(function->has_feedback_vector() &&
3023  function->IsTieringRequestedOrInProgress(),
3024  function->shared()->is_compiled());
3025  DCHECK_IMPLIES(function->HasAvailableOptimizedCode(isolate),
3026  function->shared()->is_compiled());
3027 
3028  // Reset the JSFunction if we are recompiling due to the bytecode having been
3029  // flushed.
3030  function->ResetIfCodeFlushed(isolate);
3031 
3032  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info(function->shared(), isolate);
3033 
3034  // Ensure shared function info is compiled.
3035  *is_compiled_scope = shared_info->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
3036  if (!is_compiled_scope->is_compiled() &&
3037  !Compile(isolate, shared_info, flag, is_compiled_scope)) {
3038  return false;
3039  }
3040 
3041  DCHECK(is_compiled_scope->is_compiled());
3042  DirectHandle<Code> code(shared_info->GetCode(isolate), isolate);
3043 
3044  // Initialize the feedback cell for this JSFunction and reset the interrupt
3045  // budget for feedback vector allocation even if there is a closure feedback
3046  // cell array. We are re-compiling when we have a closure feedback cell array
3047  // which means we are compiling after a bytecode flush.
3048  // TODO(verwaest/mythria): Investigate if allocating feedback vector
3049  // immediately after a flush would be better.
3050  JSFunction::InitializeFeedbackCell(isolate, function, is_compiled_scope,
3051  true);
3052  function->ResetTieringRequests();
3053 
3054  function->UpdateCode(isolate, *code);
3055 
3056  // Optimize now if --always-turbofan is enabled.
3057 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3058  if (v8_flags.always_turbofan && !function->shared()->HasAsmWasmData()) {
3059 #else
3060  if (v8_flags.always_turbofan) {
3061 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3062  DCHECK(!function->tiering_in_progress());
3063  CompilerTracer::TraceOptimizeForAlwaysOpt(isolate, function,
3064  CodeKindForTopTier());
3065 
3066  const CodeKind code_kind = CodeKindForTopTier();
3067  const ConcurrencyMode concurrency_mode = ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous;
3068 
3069  if (v8_flags.stress_concurrent_inlining &&
3070  isolate->concurrent_recompilation_enabled() &&
3071  isolate->node_observer() == nullptr) {
3072  SpawnDuplicateConcurrentJobForStressTesting(isolate, function,
3073  concurrency_mode, code_kind);
3074  }
3075 
3076  DirectHandle<Code> maybe_code;
3077  if (GetOrCompileOptimized(isolate, function, concurrency_mode, code_kind)
3078  .ToHandle(&maybe_code)) {
3079  code = maybe_code;
3080  function->UpdateOptimizedCode(isolate, *code);
3081  }
3082  }
3083 
3084  // Install a feedback vector if necessary.
3085  if (code->kind() == CodeKind::BASELINE) {
3086  JSFunction::EnsureFeedbackVector(isolate, function, is_compiled_scope);
3087  }
3088 
3089  // Check postconditions on success.
3090  DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
3091  DCHECK(function->shared()->is_compiled());
3092  DCHECK(function->is_compiled(isolate));
3093  return true;
3094 }
3095 
3096 // static
3097 bool Compiler::CompileSharedWithBaseline(Isolate* isolate,
3098  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
3099  Compiler::ClearExceptionFlag flag,
3100  IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope) {
3101  // We shouldn't be passing uncompiled functions into this function.
3102  DCHECK(is_compiled_scope->is_compiled());
3103 
3104  // Early return for already baseline-compiled functions.
3105  if (shared->HasBaselineCode()) return true;
3106 
3107  // Check if we actually can compile with baseline.
3108  if (!CanCompileWithBaseline(isolate, *shared)) return false;
3109 
3110  StackLimitCheck check(isolate);
3111  if (check.JsHasOverflowed(kStackSpaceRequiredForCompilation * KB)) {
3112  if (flag == Compiler::KEEP_EXCEPTION) {
3113  isolate->StackOverflow();
3114  }
3115  return false;
3116  }
3117 
3118  CompilerTracer::TraceStartBaselineCompile(isolate, shared);
3119  DirectHandle<Code> code;
3120  base::TimeDelta time_taken;
3121  {
3122  base::ScopedTimer timer(
3123  v8_flags.trace_baseline || v8_flags.log_function_events ? &time_taken
3124  : nullptr);
3125  if (!GenerateBaselineCode(isolate, shared).ToHandle(&code)) {
3126  // TODO(leszeks): This can only fail because of an OOM. Do we want to
3127  // report these somehow, or silently ignore them?
3128  return false;
3129  }
3130  shared->set_baseline_code(*code, kReleaseStore);
3131  shared->set_age(0);
3132  }
3133  double time_taken_ms = time_taken.InMillisecondsF();
3134 
3135  CompilerTracer::TraceFinishBaselineCompile(isolate, shared, time_taken_ms);
3136 
3137  if (IsScript(shared->script())) {
3138  LogFunctionCompilation(
3139  isolate, LogEventListener::CodeTag::kFunction,
3140  direct_handle(Cast<Script>(shared->script()), isolate), shared,
3141  DirectHandle<FeedbackVector>(), Cast<AbstractCode>(code),
3142  CodeKind::BASELINE, time_taken_ms);
3143  }
3144  return true;
3145 }
3146 
3147 // static
3148 bool Compiler::CompileBaseline(Isolate* isolate,
3149  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
3150  ClearExceptionFlag flag,
3151  IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope) {
3152  Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(function->shared(isolate), isolate);
3153  if (!CompileSharedWithBaseline(isolate, shared, flag, is_compiled_scope)) {
3154  return false;
3155  }
3156 
3157  // Baseline code needs a feedback vector.
3158  JSFunction::EnsureFeedbackVector(isolate, function, is_compiled_scope);
3159 
3160  Tagged<Code> baseline_code = shared->baseline_code(kAcquireLoad);
3161  DCHECK_EQ(baseline_code->kind(), CodeKind::BASELINE);
3162  function->UpdateCodeKeepTieringRequests(isolate, baseline_code);
3163  return true;
3164 }

3174 // static
3175 bool Compiler::FinalizeBackgroundCompileTask(BackgroundCompileTask* task,
3176  Isolate* isolate,
3177  ClearExceptionFlag flag) {
3178  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
3179  "V8.FinalizeBackgroundCompileTask");
3180  RCS_SCOPE(isolate,
3181  RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileFinalizeBackgroundCompileTask);
3182 
3183  HandleScope scope(isolate);
3184 
3185  if (!task->FinalizeFunction(isolate, flag)) return false;
3186 
3187  DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());

3191 // static
3192 void Compiler::CompileOptimized(Isolate* isolate,
3193  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
3194  ConcurrencyMode mode, CodeKind code_kind) {
3195  function->TraceOptimizationStatus("^%s", CodeKindToString(code_kind));
3196  DCHECK(CodeKindIsOptimizedJSFunction(code_kind));
3197  DCHECK(AllowCompilation::IsAllowed(isolate));
3198 
3199  if (v8_flags.stress_concurrent_inlining &&
3200  isolate->concurrent_recompilation_enabled() && IsSynchronous(mode) &&
3201  isolate->node_observer() == nullptr) {
3202  SpawnDuplicateConcurrentJobForStressTesting(isolate, function, mode,
3203  code_kind);
3204  }
3205 
3206 #ifdef DEBUG
3207  if (V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL && mode == ConcurrencyMode::kConcurrent) {
3208  DCHECK_IMPLIES(code_kind == CodeKind::MAGLEV,
3209  !function->ActiveTierIsMaglev(isolate));
3210  DCHECK_IMPLIES(code_kind == CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS,
3211  !function->ActiveTierIsTurbofan(isolate));
3212  }
3213  bool tiering_was_in_progress = function->tiering_in_progress();
3214  DCHECK_IMPLIES(tiering_was_in_progress, mode != ConcurrencyMode::kConcurrent);
3215 #endif // DEBUG
3216 
3217  DirectHandle<Code> code;
3218  if (GetOrCompileOptimized(isolate, function, mode, code_kind)
3219  .ToHandle(&code)) {
3220  function->UpdateOptimizedCode(isolate, *code);
3221  DCHECK_IMPLIES(v8_flags.log_function_events,
3222  function->IsLoggingRequested(isolate));
3223  } else {
3224 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
3225  // We can get here from CompileLazy when we have requested optimized code
3226  // which isn't yet ready. Without Leaptiering, we'll already have set the
3227  // function's code to the bytecode/baseline code on the SFI. However, in the
3228  // leaptiering case, we potentially need to do this now.
3229  if (!function->is_compiled(isolate)) {
3230  function->UpdateCodeKeepTieringRequests(
3231  isolate, function->shared()->GetCode(isolate));
3232  }
3233 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
3234  }
3235 
3236 #ifdef DEBUG
3237  DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
3238  DCHECK(function->is_compiled(isolate));
3239  DCHECK(function->shared()->HasBytecodeArray());
3240 
3241  DCHECK_IMPLIES(function->IsTieringRequestedOrInProgress() &&
3242  !function->IsLoggingRequested(isolate),
3243  function->tiering_in_progress());
3244  if (!v8_flags.always_turbofan) {
3245  // Before a maglev optimization job is started we might have to compile
3246  // bytecode. This can trigger a turbofan compilation if always_turbofan is
3247  // set. Therefore we need to skip this dcheck in that case.
3248  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!tiering_was_in_progress && function->tiering_in_progress(),
3249  function->ChecksTieringState(isolate));
3250  }
3251  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!tiering_was_in_progress && function->tiering_in_progress(),
3252  IsConcurrent(mode));
3253 #endif // DEBUG
3254 }

3260  IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope;

3264 
3265 // static
3266 MaybeDirectHandle<JSFunction> Compiler::GetFunctionFromEval(
3267  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> source,
3268  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> outer_info, DirectHandle<Context> context,
3269  LanguageMode language_mode, ParseRestriction restriction,
3270  int parameters_end_pos, int eval_position,
3271  ParsingWhileDebugging parsing_while_debugging) {
3272  // The cache lookup key needs to be aware of the separation between the
3273  // parameters and the body to prevent this valid invocation:
3274  // Function("", "function anonymous(\n/**/) {\n}");
3275  // from adding an entry that falsely approves this invalid invocation:
3276  // Function("\n/**/) {\nfunction anonymous(", "}");
3277  // The actual eval_position for indirect eval and CreateDynamicFunction
3278  // is unused (just 0), which means it's an available field to use to indicate
3279  // this separation. But to make sure we're not causing other false hits, we
3280  // negate the scope position.
3281  int eval_cache_position = eval_position;
3282  if (restriction == ONLY_SINGLE_FUNCTION_LITERAL &&
3283  parameters_end_pos != kNoSourcePosition) {
3284  // use the parameters_end_pos as the eval_position in the eval cache.
3285  DCHECK_EQ(eval_position, kNoSourcePosition);
3286  eval_cache_position = -parameters_end_pos;
3287  }
3288  CompilationCache* compilation_cache = isolate->compilation_cache();
3289  InfoCellPair eval_result = compilation_cache->LookupEval(
3290  source, outer_info, context, language_mode, eval_cache_position);
3291  if (eval_result.has_js_function()) {
3292  DirectHandle<JSFunction> result =
3293  direct_handle(eval_result.js_function(), isolate);
3294  if (v8_flags.reuse_scope_infos) {
3295  CHECK_EQ(result->context()->scope_info(), context->scope_info());
3296  }
3297  Tagged<FeedbackCell> feedback_cell = result->raw_feedback_cell();
3298  FeedbackCell::ClosureCountTransition cell_transition =
3299  feedback_cell->IncrementClosureCount(isolate);
3300  if (cell_transition == FeedbackCell::kOneToMany &&
3301  result->code(isolate)->is_context_specialized()) {
3302  result->UpdateCode(isolate, *BUILTIN_CODE(isolate, CompileLazy));
3303  }
3304  result->set_context(*context, kReleaseStore);
3305  return result;
3306  }
3307 
3308  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info;
3309  Handle<Script> script;
3310  IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope;
3311  bool allow_eval_cache;
3312  if (eval_result.has_shared()) {
3313  // Make sure that the scope_info of the context we're eval-ing in matches
3314  // the scope_info we compiled the code for.
3315  CHECK_IMPLIES(
3316  !IsNativeContext(*context),
3317  eval_result.shared()->GetOuterScopeInfo() == context->scope_info());
3318  shared_info =
3319  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo>(eval_result.shared(), isolate);
3320  script = Handle<Script>(Cast<Script>(shared_info->script()), isolate);
3321  is_compiled_scope = shared_info->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
3322  allow_eval_cache = true;
3323  } else {
3324  UnoptimizedCompileFlags flags = UnoptimizedCompileFlags::ForToplevelCompile(
3325  isolate, true, language_mode, REPLMode::kNo, ScriptType::kClassic,
3326  v8_flags.lazy_eval);
3327  flags.set_is_eval(true);
3328  flags.set_parsing_while_debugging(parsing_while_debugging);
3329  DCHECK(!flags.is_module());
3330  flags.set_parse_restriction(restriction);
3331 
3332  UnoptimizedCompileState compile_state;
3333  ReusableUnoptimizedCompileState reusable_state(isolate);
3334  ParseInfo parse_info(isolate, flags, &compile_state, &reusable_state);
3335  parse_info.set_parameters_end_pos(parameters_end_pos);
3336 
3337  MaybeDirectHandle<ScopeInfo> maybe_outer_scope_info;
3338  if (!IsNativeContext(*context)) {
3339  maybe_outer_scope_info = direct_handle(context->scope_info(), isolate);
3340  }
3341  script = parse_info.CreateScript(
3342  isolate, source, kNullMaybeHandle,
3343  OriginOptionsForEval(outer_info->script(), parsing_while_debugging));
3344  script->set_eval_from_shared(*outer_info);
3345  if (eval_position == kNoSourcePosition) {
3346  // If the position is missing, attempt to get the code offset by
3347  // walking the stack. Do not translate the code offset into source
3348  // position, but store it as negative value for lazy translation.
3349  DebuggableStackFrameIterator it(isolate);
3350  if (!it.done() && it.is_javascript()) {
3351  FrameSummary summary = it.GetTopValidFrame();
3352  script->set_eval_from_shared(
3353  summary.AsJavaScript().function()->shared());
3354  script->set_origin_options(
3355  OriginOptionsForEval(*summary.script(), parsing_while_debugging));
3356  eval_position = -summary.code_offset();
3357  } else {
3358  eval_position = 0;
3359  }
3360  }
3361  script->set_eval_from_position(eval_position);
3362 
3363  if (!v8::internal::CompileToplevel(&parse_info, script,
3364  maybe_outer_scope_info, isolate,
3365  &is_compiled_scope)
3366  .ToHandle(&shared_info)) {
3367  return MaybeDirectHandle<JSFunction>();
3368  }
3369  allow_eval_cache = parse_info.allow_eval_cache();
3370  }
3371 
3372  // If caller is strict mode, the result must be in strict mode as well.
3373  DCHECK(is_sloppy(language_mode) || is_strict(shared_info->language_mode()));
3374 
3375  DirectHandle<JSFunction> result;
3376  if (eval_result.has_shared()) {
3377  result = Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate, shared_info, context}
3378  .set_allocation_type(AllocationType::kYoung)
3379  .Build();
3380  // TODO(mythria): I don't think we need this here. PostInstantiation
3381  // already initializes feedback cell.
3382  JSFunction::InitializeFeedbackCell(isolate, result, &is_compiled_scope,
3383  true);
3384  if (allow_eval_cache) {
3385  // Make sure to cache this result.
3386  DirectHandle<FeedbackCell> new_feedback_cell(result->raw_feedback_cell(),
3387  isolate);
3388  compilation_cache->UpdateEval(source, outer_info, result, language_mode,
3389  eval_cache_position);
3390  }
3391  } else {
3392  result = Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate, shared_info, context}
3393  .set_allocation_type(AllocationType::kYoung)
3394  .Build();
3395  // TODO(mythria): I don't think we need this here. PostInstantiation
3396  // already initializes feedback cell.
3397  JSFunction::InitializeFeedbackCell(isolate, result, &is_compiled_scope,
3398  true);
3399  if (allow_eval_cache) {
3400  compilation_cache->PutEval(source, outer_info, result,
3401  eval_cache_position);
3402  }
3403  }
3404  CHECK(is_compiled_scope.is_compiled());
3405 
3406  return result;
3407 }
3408 
3409 // Check whether embedder allows code generation in this context.
3410 // (via v8::Isolate::SetModifyCodeGenerationFromStringsCallback)
3411 bool ModifyCodeGenerationFromStrings(Isolate* isolate,
3412  DirectHandle<NativeContext> context,
3413  Handle<i::Object>* source,
3414  bool is_code_like) {
3415  DCHECK(isolate->modify_code_gen_callback());
3416  DCHECK(source);
3417 
3418  // Callback set. Run it, and use the return value as source, or block
3419  // execution if it's not set.
3420  VMState<EXTERNAL> state(isolate);
3421  RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kCodeGenerationFromStringsCallbacks);
3422  ModifyCodeGenerationFromStringsResult result =
3423  isolate->modify_code_gen_callback()(v8::Utils::ToLocal(context),
3424  v8::Utils::ToLocal(*source),
3425  is_code_like);
3426  if (result.codegen_allowed && !result.modified_source.IsEmpty()) {
3427  // Use the new source (which might be the same as the old source).
3428  *source =
3429  Utils::OpenHandle(*result.modified_source.ToLocalChecked(), false);
3430  }
3431  return result.codegen_allowed;
3432 }
3433 
3434 // Run Embedder-mandated checks before generating code from a string.
3435 //
3436 // Returns a string to be used for compilation, or a flag that an object type
3437 // was encountered that is neither a string, nor something the embedder knows
3438 // how to handle.
3439 //
3440 // Returns: (assuming: std::tie(source, unknown_object))
3441 // - !source.is_null(): compilation allowed, source contains the source string.
3442 // - unknown_object is true: compilation allowed, but we don't know how to
3443 // deal with source_object.
3444 // - source.is_null() && !unknown_object: compilation should be blocked.
3445 //
3446 // - !source_is_null() and unknown_object can't be true at the same time.
3447 
3448 // static
3449 std::pair<MaybeDirectHandle<String>, bool>
3450 Compiler::ValidateDynamicCompilationSource(Isolate* isolate,
3451  DirectHandle<NativeContext> context,
3452  Handle<i::Object> original_source,
3453  bool is_code_like) {
3454  // Check if the context unconditionally allows code gen from strings.
3455  // allow_code_gen_from_strings can be many things, so we'll always check
3456  // against the 'false' literal, so that e.g. undefined and 'true' are treated
3457  // the same.
3458  if (!IsFalse(context->allow_code_gen_from_strings(), isolate) &&
3459  IsString(*original_source)) {
3460  return {Cast<String>(original_source), false};
3461  }
3462 
3463  // Check if the context wants to block or modify this source object.
3464  // Double-check that we really have a string now.
3465  // (Let modify_code_gen_callback decide, if it's been set.)
3466  if (isolate->modify_code_gen_callback()) {
3467  Handle<i::Object> modified_source = original_source;
3468  if (!ModifyCodeGenerationFromStrings(isolate, context, &modified_source,
3469  is_code_like)) {
3470  return {MaybeHandle<String>(), false};
3471  }
3472  if (!IsString(*modified_source)) {
3473  return {MaybeHandle<String>(), true};
3474  }
3475  return {Cast<String>(modified_source), false};
3476  }
3477 
3478  if (!IsFalse(context->allow_code_gen_from_strings(), isolate) &&
3479  Object::IsCodeLike(*original_source, isolate)) {
3480  // Codegen is unconditionally allowed, and we're been given a CodeLike
3481  // object. Stringify.
3482  MaybeHandle<String> stringified_source =
3483  Object::ToString(isolate, original_source);
3484  return {stringified_source, stringified_source.is_null()};
3485  }
3486 
3487  // If unconditional codegen was disabled, and no callback defined, we block
3488  // strings and allow all other objects.
3489  return {MaybeHandle<String>(), !IsString(*original_source)};
3490 }
3491 
3492 // static
3493 MaybeDirectHandle<JSFunction> Compiler::GetFunctionFromValidatedString(
3494  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context,
3495  MaybeDirectHandle<String> source, ParseRestriction restriction,
3496  int parameters_end_pos) {
3497  // Raise an EvalError if we did not receive a string.
3498  if (source.is_null()) {
3499  Handle<Object> error_message =
3500  native_context->ErrorMessageForCodeGenerationFromStrings();
3501  THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate, NewEvalError(MessageTemplate::kCodeGenFromStrings,
3502  error_message));
3503  }
3504 
3505  // Compile source string in the native context.
3506  int eval_position = kNoSourcePosition;
3507  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> outer_info(
3508  native_context->empty_function()->shared(), isolate);
3509  return Compiler::GetFunctionFromEval(
3510  isolate, source.ToHandleChecked(), outer_info, native_context,
3511  LanguageMode::kSloppy, restriction, parameters_end_pos, eval_position);
3512 }
3513 
3514 // static
3515 MaybeDirectHandle<JSFunction> Compiler::GetFunctionFromString(
3516  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<NativeContext> context,
3517  Handle<Object> source, int parameters_end_pos, bool is_code_like) {
3518  MaybeDirectHandle<String> validated_source =
3519  ValidateDynamicCompilationSource(isolate, context, source, is_code_like)
3520  .first;
3521  return GetFunctionFromValidatedString(isolate, context, validated_source,
3522  ONLY_SINGLE_FUNCTION_LITERAL,
3523  parameters_end_pos);
3524 }
