3528 struct ScriptCompileTimerScope {
3529  public:
3530  // TODO(leszeks): There are too many blink-specific entries in this enum,
3531  // figure out a way to push produce/hit-isolate-cache/consume/consume-failed
3532  // back up the API and log them in blink instead.
3533  enum class CacheBehaviour {
3534  kProduceCodeCache,
3535  kHitIsolateCacheWhenNoCache,
3536  kConsumeCodeCache,
3537  kConsumeCodeCacheFailed,
3538  kNoCacheBecauseInlineScript,
3539  kNoCacheBecauseScriptTooSmall,
3540  kNoCacheBecauseCacheTooCold,
3541  kNoCacheNoReason,
3542  kNoCacheBecauseNoResource,
3543  kNoCacheBecauseInspector,
3544  kNoCacheBecauseCachingDisabled,
3545  kNoCacheBecauseModule,
3546  kNoCacheBecauseStreamingSource,
3547  kNoCacheBecauseV8Extension,
3548  kHitIsolateCacheWhenProduceCodeCache,
3549  kHitIsolateCacheWhenConsumeCodeCache,
3550  kNoCacheBecauseExtensionModule,
3551  kNoCacheBecausePacScript,
3552  kNoCacheBecauseInDocumentWrite,
3553  kNoCacheBecauseResourceWithNoCacheHandler,
3554  kHitIsolateCacheWhenStreamingSource,
3555  kNoCacheBecauseStaticCodeCache,
3556  kCount
3557  };
3558 
3559  ScriptCompileTimerScope(
3560  Isolate* isolate, ScriptCompiler::NoCacheReason no_cache_reason,
3561  ScriptCompiler::CompilationDetails* compilation_details)
3562  : isolate_(isolate),
3563  histogram_scope_(&compilation_details->foreground_time_in_microseconds),
3564  all_scripts_histogram_scope_(isolate->counters()->compile_script()),
3565  no_cache_reason_(no_cache_reason),
3566  hit_isolate_cache_(false),
3567  consuming_code_cache_(false),
3568  consuming_code_cache_failed_(false) {}
3569 
3570  ~ScriptCompileTimerScope() {
3571  CacheBehaviour cache_behaviour = GetCacheBehaviour();
3572 
3573  Histogram* cache_behaviour_histogram =
3574  isolate_->counters()->compile_script_cache_behaviour();
3575  // Sanity check that the histogram has exactly one bin per enum entry.
3576  DCHECK_EQ(0, cache_behaviour_histogram->min());
3577  DCHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(CacheBehaviour::kCount),
3578  cache_behaviour_histogram->max() + 1);
3579  DCHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(CacheBehaviour::kCount),
3580  cache_behaviour_histogram->num_buckets());
3581  cache_behaviour_histogram->AddSample(static_cast<int>(cache_behaviour));
3582 
3583  histogram_scope_.set_histogram(
3584  GetCacheBehaviourTimedHistogram(cache_behaviour));
3585  }
3586 
3587  void set_hit_isolate_cache() { hit_isolate_cache_ = true; }
3588 
3589  void set_consuming_code_cache() { consuming_code_cache_ = true; }
3590 
3591  void set_consuming_code_cache_failed() {
3592  consuming_code_cache_failed_ = true;
3593  }
3594 
3595  private:
3596  Isolate* isolate_;
3597  LazyTimedHistogramScope histogram_scope_;
3598  // TODO(leszeks): This timer is the sum of the other times, consider removing
3599  // it to save space.
3600  NestedTimedHistogramScope all_scripts_histogram_scope_;
3601  ScriptCompiler::NoCacheReason no_cache_reason_;
3602  bool hit_isolate_cache_;
3603  bool consuming_code_cache_;
3604  bool consuming_code_cache_failed_;
3605 
3606  CacheBehaviour GetCacheBehaviour() {
3607  if (consuming_code_cache_) {
3608  if (hit_isolate_cache_) {
3609  return CacheBehaviour::kHitIsolateCacheWhenConsumeCodeCache;
3610  } else if (consuming_code_cache_failed_) {
3611  return CacheBehaviour::kConsumeCodeCacheFailed;
3612  }
3613  return CacheBehaviour::kConsumeCodeCache;
3614  }
3615 
3616  if (hit_isolate_cache_) {
3617  // A roundabout way of knowing the embedder is going to produce a code
3618  // cache (which is done by a separate API call later) is to check whether
3619  // no_cache_reason_ is
3620  // ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseDeferredProduceCodeCache.
3621  if (no_cache_reason_ ==
3622  ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseDeferredProduceCodeCache) {
3623  return CacheBehaviour::kHitIsolateCacheWhenProduceCodeCache;
3624  } else if (no_cache_reason_ ==
3625  ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseStreamingSource) {
3626  return CacheBehaviour::kHitIsolateCacheWhenStreamingSource;
3627  }
3628  return CacheBehaviour::kHitIsolateCacheWhenNoCache;
3629  }
3630 
3631  switch (no_cache_reason_) {
3632  case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseInlineScript:
3633  return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseInlineScript;
3634  case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseScriptTooSmall:
3635  return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseScriptTooSmall;
3636  case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseCacheTooCold:
3637  return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseCacheTooCold;
3638  case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheNoReason:
3639  return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheNoReason;
3640  case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseNoResource:
3641  return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseNoResource;
3642  case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseInspector:
3643  return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseInspector;
3644  case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseCachingDisabled:
3645  return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseCachingDisabled;
3646  case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseModule:
3647  return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseModule;
3648  case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseStreamingSource:
3649  return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseStreamingSource;
3650  case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseV8Extension:
3651  return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseV8Extension;
3652  case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseExtensionModule:
3653  return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseExtensionModule;
3654  case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecausePacScript:
3655  return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecausePacScript;
3656  case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseInDocumentWrite:
3657  return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseInDocumentWrite;
3658  case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseResourceWithNoCacheHandler:
3659  return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseResourceWithNoCacheHandler;
3660  case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseDeferredProduceCodeCache:
3661  return CacheBehaviour::kProduceCodeCache;
3662  case ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseStaticCodeCache:
3663  return CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseStaticCodeCache;
3664  }
3665  UNREACHABLE();
3666  }
3667 
3668  TimedHistogram* GetCacheBehaviourTimedHistogram(
3669  CacheBehaviour cache_behaviour) {
3670  switch (cache_behaviour) {
3671  case CacheBehaviour::kProduceCodeCache:
3672  // Even if we hit the isolate's compilation cache, we currently recompile
3673  // when we want to produce the code cache.
3674  case CacheBehaviour::kHitIsolateCacheWhenProduceCodeCache:
3675  return isolate_->counters()->compile_script_with_produce_cache();
3676  case CacheBehaviour::kHitIsolateCacheWhenNoCache:
3677  case CacheBehaviour::kHitIsolateCacheWhenConsumeCodeCache:
3678  case CacheBehaviour::kHitIsolateCacheWhenStreamingSource:
3679  return isolate_->counters()->compile_script_with_isolate_cache_hit();
3680  case CacheBehaviour::kConsumeCodeCacheFailed:
3681  return isolate_->counters()->compile_script_consume_failed();
3682  case CacheBehaviour::kConsumeCodeCache:
3683  return isolate_->counters()->compile_script_with_consume_cache();
3684 
3685  // Note that this only counts the finalization part of streaming, the
3686  // actual streaming compile is counted by BackgroundCompileTask into
3687  // "compile_script_on_background".
3688  case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseStreamingSource:
3689  return isolate_->counters()->compile_script_streaming_finalization();
3690 
3691  case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseInlineScript:
3692  return isolate_->counters()
3693  ->compile_script_no_cache_because_inline_script();
3694  case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseScriptTooSmall:
3695  return isolate_->counters()
3696  ->compile_script_no_cache_because_script_too_small();
3697  case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseCacheTooCold:
3698  return isolate_->counters()
3699  ->compile_script_no_cache_because_cache_too_cold();
3700 
3701  // Aggregate all the other "no cache" counters into a single histogram, to
3702  // save space.
3703  case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheNoReason:
3704  case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseNoResource:
3705  case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseInspector:
3706  case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseCachingDisabled:
3707  // TODO(leszeks): Consider counting separately once modules are more
3708  // common.
3709  case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseModule:
3710  case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseV8Extension:
3711  case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseExtensionModule:
3712  case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecausePacScript:
3713  case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseInDocumentWrite:
3714  case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseResourceWithNoCacheHandler:
3715  case CacheBehaviour::kNoCacheBecauseStaticCodeCache:
3716  return isolate_->counters()->compile_script_no_cache_other();
3717 
3718  case CacheBehaviour::kCount:
3719  UNREACHABLE();
3720  }
3721  UNREACHABLE();
3722  }
3723 };
3724 
3725 Handle<Script> NewScript(Isolate* isolate, ParseInfo* parse_info,
3726  DirectHandle<String> source,
3727  ScriptDetails script_details, NativesFlag natives) {
3728  // Create a script object describing the script to be compiled.
3729  Handle<Script> script = parse_info->CreateScript(
3730  isolate, source, script_details.wrapped_arguments,
3731  script_details.origin_options, natives);
3732  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3733  SetScriptFieldsFromDetails(isolate, *script, script_details, &no_gc);
3734  LOG(isolate, ScriptDetails(*script));
3735  return script;
3736 }

3738 MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> CompileScriptOnMainThread(
3739  const UnoptimizedCompileFlags flags, DirectHandle<String> source,
3740  const ScriptDetails& script_details, NativesFlag natives,
3741  v8::Extension* extension, Isolate* isolate,
3742  MaybeHandle<Script> maybe_script, IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope,
3743  CompileHintCallback compile_hint_callback = nullptr,
3744  void* compile_hint_callback_data = nullptr) {
3745  UnoptimizedCompileState compile_state;
3746  ReusableUnoptimizedCompileState reusable_state(isolate);
3747  ParseInfo parse_info(isolate, flags, &compile_state, &reusable_state);
3748  parse_info.set_extension(extension);
3749  parse_info.SetCompileHintCallbackAndData(compile_hint_callback,
3750  compile_hint_callback_data);
3751 
3752  Handle<Script> script;
3753  if (!maybe_script.ToHandle(&script)) {
3754  script = NewScript(isolate, &parse_info, source, script_details, natives);
3755  }
3756  DCHECK_EQ(parse_info.flags().is_repl_mode(), script->is_repl_mode());
3757 
3758  return Compiler::CompileToplevel(&parse_info, script, isolate,
3759  is_compiled_scope);
3760 }

3762 class StressBackgroundCompileThread : public ParkingThread {
3763  public:
3764  StressBackgroundCompileThread(Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> source,
3765  const ScriptDetails& script_details)
3766  : ParkingThread(
3767  base::Thread::Options("StressBackgroundCompileThread", 2 * i::MB)),
3768  source_(source),
3769  streamed_source_(std::make_unique<SourceStream>(source, isolate),
3770  v8::ScriptCompiler::StreamedSource::TWO_BYTE) {
3771  ScriptType type = script_details.origin_options.IsModule()
3772  ? ScriptType::kModule
3773  : ScriptType::kClassic;
3774  data()->task = std::make_unique<i::BackgroundCompileTask>(
3775  data(), isolate, type,
3776  ScriptCompiler::CompileOptions::kNoCompileOptions,
3777  &streamed_source_.compilation_details());
3778  }
3779 
3780  void Run() override { data()->task->Run(); }
3781 
3782  ScriptStreamingData* data() { return streamed_source_.impl(); }
3783 
3784  private:
3785  // Dummy external source stream which returns the whole source in one go.
3786  // TODO(leszeks): Also test chunking the data.
3787  class SourceStream : public v8::ScriptCompiler::ExternalSourceStream {
3788  public:
3789  SourceStream(DirectHandle<String> source, Isolate* isolate) : done_(false) {
3790  source_length_ = source->length();
3791  source_buffer_ = std::make_unique<uint16_t[]>(source_length_);
3792  String::WriteToFlat(*source, source_buffer_.get(), 0, source_length_);
3793  }
3794 
3795  size_t GetMoreData(const uint8_t** src) override {
3796  if (done_) {
3797  return 0;
3798  }
3799  *src = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(source_buffer_.release());
3800  done_ = true;
3801 
3802  return source_length_ * 2;
3803  }
3804 
3805  private:
3806  uint32_t source_length_;
3807  std::unique_ptr<uint16_t[]> source_buffer_;
3808  bool done_;
3809  };
3810 
3811  Handle<String> source_;
3812  v8::ScriptCompiler::StreamedSource streamed_source_;
3813 };
3814 
3815 bool CanBackgroundCompile(const ScriptDetails& script_details,
3816  v8::Extension* extension,
3817  ScriptCompiler::CompileOptions compile_options,
3818  NativesFlag natives) {
3819  // TODO(leszeks): Remove the module check once background compilation of
3820  // modules is supported.
3821  return !script_details.origin_options.IsModule() && !extension &&
3822  script_details.repl_mode == REPLMode::kNo &&
3823  (compile_options == ScriptCompiler::kNoCompileOptions) &&
3824  natives == NOT_NATIVES_CODE;
3825 }
3826 
3827 bool CompilationExceptionIsRangeError(Isolate* isolate,
3828  DirectHandle<Object> obj) {
3829  if (!IsJSError(*obj, isolate)) return false;
3830  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> js_obj = Cast<JSReceiver>(obj);
3831  DirectHandle<JSReceiver> constructor;
3832  if (!JSReceiver::GetConstructor(isolate, js_obj).ToHandle(&constructor)) {
3833  return false;
3834  }
3835  return *constructor == *isolate->range_error_function();
3836 }
3837 
3838 MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo>
3839 CompileScriptOnBothBackgroundAndMainThread(Handle<String> source,
3840  const ScriptDetails& script_details,
3841  Isolate* isolate,
3842  IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope) {
3843  // Start a background thread compiling the script.
3844  StressBackgroundCompileThread background_compile_thread(isolate, source,
3845  script_details);
3846 
3847  UnoptimizedCompileFlags flags_copy =
3848  background_compile_thread.data()->task->flags();
3849 
3850  CHECK(background_compile_thread.Start());
3851  MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> main_thread_maybe_result;
3852  bool main_thread_had_stack_overflow = false;
3853  // In parallel, compile on the main thread to flush out any data races.
3854  {
3855  IsCompiledScope inner_is_compiled_scope;
3856  // The background thread should also create any relevant exceptions, so we
3857  // can ignore the main-thread created ones.
3858  // TODO(leszeks): Maybe verify that any thrown (or unthrown) exceptions are
3859  // equivalent.
3860  TryCatch ignore_try_catch(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(isolate));
3861  flags_copy.set_script_id(Script::kTemporaryScriptId);
3862  main_thread_maybe_result = CompileScriptOnMainThread(
3863  flags_copy, source, script_details, NOT_NATIVES_CODE, nullptr, isolate,
3864  MaybeHandle<Script>(), &inner_is_compiled_scope);
3865  if (main_thread_maybe_result.is_null()) {
3866  // Assume all range errors are stack overflows.
3867  main_thread_had_stack_overflow = CompilationExceptionIsRangeError(
3868  isolate, direct_handle(isolate->exception(), isolate));
3869  isolate->clear_exception();
3870  }
3871  }
3872 
3873  // Join with background thread and finalize compilation.
3874  background_compile_thread.ParkedJoin(isolate->main_thread_local_isolate());
3875 
3876  ScriptCompiler::CompilationDetails compilation_details;
3877  MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_result =
3878  Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfoForStreamedScript(
3879  isolate, source, script_details, background_compile_thread.data(),
3880  is_compiled_scope, &compilation_details);
3881 
3882  // Either both compiles should succeed, or both should fail. The one exception
3883  // to this is that the main-thread compilation might stack overflow while the
3884  // background compilation doesn't, so relax the check to include this case.
3885  // TODO(leszeks): Compare the contents of the results of the two compiles.
3886  if (main_thread_had_stack_overflow) {
3887  CHECK(main_thread_maybe_result.is_null());
3888  } else {
3889  CHECK_EQ(maybe_result.is_null(), main_thread_maybe_result.is_null());
3890  }
3891 
3892  return maybe_result;
3893 }
3894 
3895 namespace {
3896 ScriptCompiler::InMemoryCacheResult CategorizeLookupResult(
3897  const CompilationCacheScript::LookupResult& lookup_result) {
3898  return !lookup_result.toplevel_sfi().is_null()
3899  ? ScriptCompiler::InMemoryCacheResult::kHit
3900  : !lookup_result.script().is_null()
3901  ? ScriptCompiler::InMemoryCacheResult::kPartial
3902  : ScriptCompiler::InMemoryCacheResult::kMiss;
3903 }
3904 } // namespace
3905 
3906 MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> GetSharedFunctionInfoForScriptImpl(
3907  Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> source,
3908  const ScriptDetails& script_details, v8::Extension* extension,
3909  AlignedCachedData* cached_data, BackgroundDeserializeTask* deserialize_task,
3910  v8::CompileHintCallback compile_hint_callback,
3911  void* compile_hint_callback_data,
3912  ScriptCompiler::CompileOptions compile_options,
3913  ScriptCompiler::NoCacheReason no_cache_reason, NativesFlag natives,
3914  ScriptCompiler::CompilationDetails* compilation_details) {
3915  ScriptCompileTimerScope compile_timer(isolate, no_cache_reason,
3916  compilation_details);
3917 
3918  if (compile_options & ScriptCompiler::kConsumeCodeCache) {
3919  // Have to have exactly one of cached_data or deserialize_task.
3920  DCHECK(cached_data || deserialize_task);
3921  DCHECK(!(cached_data && deserialize_task));
3922  DCHECK_NULL(extension);
3923  } else {
3924  DCHECK_NULL(cached_data);
3925  DCHECK_NULL(deserialize_task);
3926  }
3927 
3928  if (compile_options & ScriptCompiler::kConsumeCompileHints) {
3929  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(compile_hint_callback);
3930  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(compile_hint_callback_data);
3931  } else {
3932  DCHECK_NULL(compile_hint_callback);
3933  DCHECK_NULL(compile_hint_callback_data);
3934  }
3935 
3936  compilation_details->background_time_in_microseconds =
3937  deserialize_task ? deserialize_task->background_time_in_microseconds()
3938  : 0;
3939 
3940  LanguageMode language_mode = construct_language_mode(v8_flags.use_strict);
3941  CompilationCache* compilation_cache = isolate->compilation_cache();
3942 
3943  // For extensions or REPL mode scripts neither do a compilation cache lookup,
3944  // nor put the compilation result back into the cache.
3945  const bool use_compilation_cache =
3946  extension == nullptr && script_details.repl_mode == REPLMode::kNo;
3947  MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_result;
3948  MaybeHandle<Script> maybe_script;
3949  IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope;
3950  if (use_compilation_cache) {
3951  bool can_consume_code_cache =
3952  compile_options & ScriptCompiler::kConsumeCodeCache;
3953  if (can_consume_code_cache) {
3954  compile_timer.set_consuming_code_cache();
3955  }
3956 
3957  // First check per-isolate compilation cache.
3958  CompilationCacheScript::LookupResult lookup_result =
3959  compilation_cache->LookupScript(source, script_details, language_mode);
3960  compilation_details->in_memory_cache_result =
3961  CategorizeLookupResult(lookup_result);
3962  maybe_script = lookup_result.script();
3963  maybe_result = lookup_result.toplevel_sfi();
3964  is_compiled_scope = lookup_result.is_compiled_scope();
3965  if (!maybe_result.is_null()) {
3966  compile_timer.set_hit_isolate_cache();
3967  } else if (can_consume_code_cache) {
3968  compile_timer.set_consuming_code_cache();
3969  // Then check cached code provided by embedder.
3970  NestedTimedHistogramScope timer(
3971  isolate->counters()->compile_deserialize());
3972  RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileDeserialize);
3973  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
3974  "V8.CompileDeserialize");
3975  if (deserialize_task) {
3976  // If there's a cache consume task, finish it.
3977  maybe_result =
3978  deserialize_task->Finish(isolate, source, script_details);
3979  // It is possible at this point that there is a Script object for this
3980  // script in the compilation cache (held in the variable maybe_script),
3981  // which does not match maybe_result->script(). This could happen any of
3982  // three ways:
3983  // 1. The embedder didn't call MergeWithExistingScript.
3984  // 2. At the time the embedder called SourceTextAvailable, there was not
3985  // yet a Script in the compilation cache, but it arrived sometime
3986  // later.
3987  // 3. At the time the embedder called SourceTextAvailable, there was a
3988  // Script available, and the new content has been merged into that
3989  // Script. However, since then, the Script was replaced in the
3990  // compilation cache, such as by another evaluation of the script
3991  // hitting case 2, or DevTools clearing the cache.
3992  // This is okay; the new Script object will replace the current Script
3993  // held by the compilation cache. Both Scripts may remain in use
3994  // indefinitely, causing increased memory usage, but these cases are
3995  // sufficiently unlikely, and ensuring a correct merge in the third case
3996  // would be non-trivial.
3997  } else {
3998  maybe_result = CodeSerializer::Deserialize(
3999  isolate, cached_data, source, script_details, maybe_script);
4000  }
4001 
4002  bool consuming_code_cache_succeeded = false;
4003  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result;
4004  if (maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
4005  is_compiled_scope = result->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
4006  if (is_compiled_scope.is_compiled()) {
4007  consuming_code_cache_succeeded = true;
4008  // Promote to per-isolate compilation cache.
4009  compilation_cache->PutScript(source, language_mode, result);
4010  }
4011  }
4012  if (!consuming_code_cache_succeeded) {
4013  // Deserializer failed. Fall through to compile.
4014  compile_timer.set_consuming_code_cache_failed();
4015  }
4016  }
4017  }
4018 
4019  if (maybe_result.is_null()) {
4020  // No cache entry found compile the script.
4021  if (v8_flags.stress_background_compile &&
4022  CanBackgroundCompile(script_details, extension, compile_options,
4023  natives)) {
4024  // If the --stress-background-compile flag is set, do the actual
4025  // compilation on a background thread, and wait for its result.
4026  maybe_result = CompileScriptOnBothBackgroundAndMainThread(
4027  source, script_details, isolate, &is_compiled_scope);
4028  } else {
4029  UnoptimizedCompileFlags flags =
4030  UnoptimizedCompileFlags::ForToplevelCompile(
4031  isolate, natives == NOT_NATIVES_CODE, language_mode,
4032  script_details.repl_mode,
4033  script_details.origin_options.IsModule() ? ScriptType::kModule
4034  : ScriptType::kClassic,
4035  v8_flags.lazy);
4036 
4037  flags.set_is_eager(compile_options & ScriptCompiler::kEagerCompile);
4038  flags.set_compile_hints_magic_enabled(
4039  compile_options & ScriptCompiler::kFollowCompileHintsMagicComment);
4040  flags.set_compile_hints_per_function_magic_enabled(
4041  compile_options &
4042  ScriptCompiler::kFollowCompileHintsPerFunctionMagicComment);
4043 
4044  if (DirectHandle<Script> script; maybe_script.ToHandle(&script)) {
4045  flags.set_script_id(script->id());
4046  }
4047 
4048  maybe_result = CompileScriptOnMainThread(
4049  flags, source, script_details, natives, extension, isolate,
4050  maybe_script, &is_compiled_scope, compile_hint_callback,
4051  compile_hint_callback_data);
4052  }
4053 
4054  // Add the result to the isolate cache.
4055  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result;
4056  if (use_compilation_cache && maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
4057  DCHECK(is_compiled_scope.is_compiled());
4058  compilation_cache->PutScript(source, language_mode, result);
4059  } else if (maybe_result.is_null() && natives != EXTENSION_CODE) {
4060  isolate->ReportPendingMessages();
4061  }
4062  }
4063  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result;
4064  if (compile_options & ScriptCompiler::CompileOptions::kProduceCompileHints &&
4065  maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
4066  Cast<Script>(result->script())->set_produce_compile_hints(true);
4067  }
4068 
4069  return maybe_result;
4070 }
4071 
4072 } // namespace

4138 // static
4139 MaybeDirectHandle<JSFunction> Compiler::GetWrappedFunction(
4140  Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> source, DirectHandle<Context> context,
4141  const ScriptDetails& script_details, AlignedCachedData* cached_data,
4142  v8::ScriptCompiler::CompileOptions compile_options,
4143  v8::ScriptCompiler::NoCacheReason no_cache_reason) {
4144  ScriptCompiler::CompilationDetails compilation_details;
4145  ScriptCompileTimerScope compile_timer(isolate, no_cache_reason,
4146  &compilation_details);
4147 
4148  if (compile_options & ScriptCompiler::kConsumeCodeCache) {
4149  DCHECK(cached_data);
4150  DCHECK_EQ(script_details.repl_mode, REPLMode::kNo);
4151  } else {
4152  DCHECK_NULL(cached_data);
4153  }
4154 
4155  LanguageMode language_mode = construct_language_mode(v8_flags.use_strict);
4156  DCHECK(!script_details.wrapped_arguments.is_null());
4157  MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_result;
4158  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result;
4159  Handle<Script> script;
4160  IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope;
4161  bool can_consume_code_cache =
4162  compile_options & ScriptCompiler::kConsumeCodeCache;
4163  CompilationCache* compilation_cache = isolate->compilation_cache();
4164  // First check per-isolate compilation cache.
4165  CompilationCacheScript::LookupResult lookup_result =
4166  compilation_cache->LookupScript(source, script_details, language_mode);
4167  maybe_result = lookup_result.toplevel_sfi();
4168  if (maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
4169  is_compiled_scope = result->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
4170  compile_timer.set_hit_isolate_cache();
4171  } else if (can_consume_code_cache) {
4172  compile_timer.set_consuming_code_cache();
4173  // Then check cached code provided by embedder.
4174  NestedTimedHistogramScope timer(isolate->counters()->compile_deserialize());
4175  RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompileDeserialize);
4176  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
4177  "V8.CompileDeserialize");
4178  maybe_result = CodeSerializer::Deserialize(isolate, cached_data, source,
4179  script_details);
4180  bool consuming_code_cache_succeeded = false;
4181  if (maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
4182  is_compiled_scope = result->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
4183  if (is_compiled_scope.is_compiled()) {
4184  consuming_code_cache_succeeded = true;
4185  // Promote to per-isolate compilation cache.
4186  compilation_cache->PutScript(source, language_mode, result);
4187  }
4188  }
4189  if (!consuming_code_cache_succeeded) {
4190  // Deserializer failed. Fall through to compile.
4191  compile_timer.set_consuming_code_cache_failed();
4192  }
4193  }
4194 
4195  if (maybe_result.is_null()) {
4196  UnoptimizedCompileFlags flags = UnoptimizedCompileFlags::ForToplevelCompile(
4197  isolate, true, language_mode, script_details.repl_mode,
4198  ScriptType::kClassic, v8_flags.lazy);
4199  flags.set_is_eval(true); // Use an eval scope as declaration scope.
4200  flags.set_function_syntax_kind(FunctionSyntaxKind::kWrapped);
4201  // TODO(delphick): Remove this and instead make the wrapped and wrapper
4202  // functions fully non-lazy instead thus preventing source positions from
4203  // being omitted.
4204  flags.set_collect_source_positions(true);
4205  flags.set_is_eager(compile_options & ScriptCompiler::kEagerCompile);
4206 
4207  UnoptimizedCompileState compile_state;
4208  ReusableUnoptimizedCompileState reusable_state(isolate);
4209  ParseInfo parse_info(isolate, flags, &compile_state, &reusable_state);
4210 
4211  MaybeDirectHandle<ScopeInfo> maybe_outer_scope_info;
4212  if (!IsNativeContext(*context)) {
4213  maybe_outer_scope_info = direct_handle(context->scope_info(), isolate);
4214  }
4215  script = NewScript(isolate, &parse_info, source, script_details,
4216  NOT_NATIVES_CODE);
4217 
4218  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> top_level;
4219  maybe_result = v8::internal::CompileToplevel(&parse_info, script,
4220  maybe_outer_scope_info,
4221  isolate, &is_compiled_scope);
4222  if (maybe_result.is_null()) isolate->ReportPendingMessages();
4223  ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, top_level, maybe_result);
4224 
4225  SharedFunctionInfo::ScriptIterator infos(isolate, *script);
4226  for (Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> info = infos.Next(); !info.is_null();
4227  info = infos.Next()) {
4228  if (info->is_wrapped()) {
4229  result = direct_handle(info, isolate);
4230  break;
4231  }
4232  }
4233  DCHECK(!result.is_null());
4234 
4235  is_compiled_scope = result->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
4236  script = Handle<Script>(Cast<Script>(result->script()), isolate);
4237  // Add the result to the isolate cache if there's no context extension.
4238  if (maybe_outer_scope_info.is_null()) {
4239  compilation_cache->PutScript(source, language_mode, result);
4240  }
4241  }
4242 
4243  DCHECK(is_compiled_scope.is_compiled());
4244 
4245  return Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate, result, context}
4246  .set_allocation_type(AllocationType::kYoung)
4247  .Build();
4248 }

4250 // static
4251 MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo>
4252 Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfoForStreamedScript(
4253  Isolate* isolate, Handle<String> source,
4254  const ScriptDetails& script_details, ScriptStreamingData* streaming_data,
4255  IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope,
4256  ScriptCompiler::CompilationDetails* compilation_details) {
4257  DCHECK(!script_details.origin_options.IsWasm());
4258 
4259  ScriptCompileTimerScope compile_timer(
4260  isolate, ScriptCompiler::kNoCacheBecauseStreamingSource,
4261  compilation_details);
4262  PostponeInterruptsScope postpone(isolate);
4263 
4264  BackgroundCompileTask* task = streaming_data->task.get();
4265 
4266  MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_result;
4267  MaybeDirectHandle<Script> maybe_cached_script;
4268  // Check if compile cache already holds the SFI, if so no need to finalize
4269  // the code compiled on the background thread.
4270  CompilationCache* compilation_cache = isolate->compilation_cache();
4271  {
4272  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
4273  "V8.StreamingFinalization.CheckCache");
4274  CompilationCacheScript::LookupResult lookup_result =
4275  compilation_cache->LookupScript(source, script_details,
4276  task->flags().outer_language_mode());
4277  compilation_details->in_memory_cache_result =
4278  CategorizeLookupResult(lookup_result);
4279  *is_compiled_scope = lookup_result.is_compiled_scope();
4280 
4281  if (!lookup_result.toplevel_sfi().is_null()) {
4282  maybe_result = lookup_result.toplevel_sfi();
4283  }
4284 
4285  if (!maybe_result.is_null()) {
4286  compile_timer.set_hit_isolate_cache();
4287  } else {
4288  maybe_cached_script = lookup_result.script();
4289  }
4290  }
4291 
4292  if (maybe_result.is_null()) {
4293  // No cache entry found, finalize compilation of the script and add it to
4294  // the isolate cache.
4295  RCS_SCOPE(isolate,
4296  RuntimeCallCounterId::kCompilePublishBackgroundFinalization);
4297  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
4298  "V8.OffThreadFinalization.Publish");
4299 
4300  maybe_result = task->FinalizeScript(isolate, source, script_details,
4301  maybe_cached_script);
4302 
4303  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result;
4304  if (maybe_result.ToHandle(&result)) {
4305  // Get a new is_compiled_scope off the result before the task's data
4306  // (including the persistent handles owned by its IsCompiledScope) are
4307  // released.
4308  *is_compiled_scope = result->is_compiled_scope(isolate);
4309 
4310  if (task->flags().produce_compile_hints()) {
4311  Cast<Script>(result->script())->set_produce_compile_hints(true);
4312  }
4313 
4314  // Add compiled code to the isolate cache.
4315  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
4316  "V8.StreamingFinalization.AddToCache");
4317  compilation_cache->PutScript(source, task->flags().outer_language_mode(),
4318  result);
4319  }
4320  }
4321 
4322  TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
4323  "V8.StreamingFinalization.Release");
4324  streaming_data->Release();
4325  return maybe_result;
4326 } // namespace internal
4327 
4328 // static
4329 template <typename IsolateT>
4330 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfo(
4331  FunctionLiteral* literal, DirectHandle<Script> script, IsolateT* isolate) {
4332  // If we're parallel compiling functions, we might already have attached a SFI
4333  // to this literal.
4334  if (!literal->shared_function_info().is_null()) {
4335  return literal->shared_function_info();
4336  }
4337  // Precondition: code has been parsed and scopes have been analyzed.
4338  MaybeDirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_existing;
4339 
4340  // Find any previously allocated shared function info for the given literal.
4341  maybe_existing = Script::FindSharedFunctionInfo(script, isolate, literal);
4342 
4343  // If we found an existing shared function info, return it.
4344  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> existing;
4345  if (maybe_existing.ToHandle(&existing)) {
4346  // If the function has been uncompiled (bytecode flushed) it will have lost
4347  // any preparsed data. If we produced preparsed data during this compile for
4348  // this function, replace the uncompiled data with one that includes it.
4349  if (literal->produced_preparse_data() != nullptr &&
4350  existing->HasUncompiledDataWithoutPreparseData(isolate)) {
4351  DirectHandle<UncompiledData> existing_uncompiled_data(
4352  existing->uncompiled_data(isolate), isolate);
4353  DCHECK_EQ(literal->start_position(),
4354  existing_uncompiled_data->start_position());
4355  DCHECK_EQ(literal->end_position(),
4356  existing_uncompiled_data->end_position());
4357  // Use existing uncompiled data's inferred name as it may be more
4358  // accurate than the literal we preparsed.
4359  Handle<String> inferred_name =
4360  handle(existing_uncompiled_data->inferred_name(), isolate);
4361  Handle<PreparseData> preparse_data =
4362  literal->produced_preparse_data()->Serialize(isolate);
4363  DirectHandle<UncompiledData> new_uncompiled_data =
4364  isolate->factory()->NewUncompiledDataWithPreparseData(
4365  inferred_name, existing_uncompiled_data->start_position(),
4366  existing_uncompiled_data->end_position(), preparse_data);
4367  existing->set_uncompiled_data(*new_uncompiled_data);
4368  }
4369  return existing;
4370  }
4371 
4372  // Allocate a shared function info object which will be compiled lazily.
4373  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> result =
4374  isolate->factory()->NewSharedFunctionInfoForLiteral(literal, script,
4375  false);
4376  return result;
4377 }
4378 
4379 template DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfo(
4380  FunctionLiteral* literal, DirectHandle<Script> script, Isolate* isolate);
4381 template DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfo(
4382  FunctionLiteral* literal, DirectHandle<Script> script,
4383  LocalIsolate* isolate);
4384 
4385 // static
4386 MaybeHandle<Code> Compiler::CompileOptimizedOSR(
4387  Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
4388  BytecodeOffset osr_offset, ConcurrencyMode mode, CodeKind code_kind) {
4389  DCHECK(IsOSR(osr_offset));
4390 
4391  if (V8_UNLIKELY(isolate->serializer_enabled())) return {};
4392  if (V8_UNLIKELY(function->shared()->optimization_disabled(code_kind)))
4393  return {};
4394 
4395  // TODO(chromium:1031479): Currently, OSR triggering mechanism is tied to the
4396  // bytecode array. So, it might be possible to mark closure in one native
4397  // context and optimize a closure from a different native context. So check if
4398  // there is a feedback vector before OSRing. We don't expect this to happen
4399  // often.
4400  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!function->has_feedback_vector())) return {};
4401 
4402  CompilerTracer::TraceOptimizeOSRStarted(isolate, function, osr_offset, mode);
4403  MaybeHandle<Code> result =
4404  GetOrCompileOptimized(isolate, function, mode, code_kind, osr_offset);
4405 
4406  if (result.is_null()) {
4407  CompilerTracer::TraceOptimizeOSRUnavailable(isolate, function, osr_offset,
4408  mode);
4409  } else {
4410  DCHECK_GE(result.ToHandleChecked()->kind(), CodeKind::MAGLEV);
4411  CompilerTracer::TraceOptimizeOSRAvailable(isolate, function, osr_offset,
4412  mode);
4413  }
4414 
4415  return result;
4416 }
4417 
4418 // static
4419 void Compiler::DisposeTurbofanCompilationJob(Isolate* isolate,
4420  TurbofanCompilationJob* job) {
4421  TRACE_EVENT_WITH_FLOW0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
4422  "V8.OptimizeConcurrentDispose", job->trace_id(),
4423  TRACE_EVENT_FLAG_FLOW_IN);
4424  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function = job->compilation_info()->closure();
4425  function->SetTieringInProgress(isolate, false,
4426  job->compilation_info()->osr_offset());
4427 }
4428 
4429 // static
4430 void Compiler::FinalizeTurbofanCompilationJob(TurbofanCompilationJob* job,
4431  Isolate* isolate) {
4432  VMState<COMPILER> state(isolate);
4433  OptimizedCompilationInfo* compilation_info = job->compilation_info();
4434 
4435  TimerEventScope<TimerEventRecompileSynchronous> timer(isolate);
4436  RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kOptimizeConcurrentFinalize);
4437  TRACE_EVENT_WITH_FLOW0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
4438  "V8.OptimizeConcurrentFinalize", job->trace_id(),
4439  TRACE_EVENT_FLAG_FLOW_IN | TRACE_EVENT_FLAG_FLOW_OUT);
4440 
4441  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function = compilation_info->closure();
4442  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = compilation_info->shared_info();
4443 
4444  const bool use_result = !compilation_info->discard_result_for_testing();
4445  const BytecodeOffset osr_offset = compilation_info->osr_offset();
4446 
4447  DCHECK(!shared->HasBreakInfo(isolate));
4448 
4449  // 1) Optimization on the concurrent thread may have failed.
4450  // 2) The function may have already been optimized by OSR. Simply continue.
4451  // Except when OSR already disabled optimization for some reason.
4452  // 3) The code may have already been invalidated due to dependency change.
4453  // 4) InstructionStream generation may have failed.
4454  if (job->state() == CompilationJob::State::kReadyToFinalize) {
4455  if (shared->optimization_disabled(CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS)) {
4456  job->RetryOptimization(shared->disabled_optimization_reason());
4457  } else if (job->FinalizeJob(isolate) == CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED) {
4458  job->RecordCompilationStats(ConcurrencyMode::kConcurrent, isolate);
4459  job->RecordFunctionCompilation(LogEventListener::CodeTag::kFunction,
4460  isolate);
4461  if (V8_LIKELY(use_result)) {
4462  function->SetTieringInProgress(isolate, false,
4463  job->compilation_info()->osr_offset());
4464  if (!V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL || IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
4465  OptimizedCodeCache::Insert(
4466  isolate, *compilation_info->closure(),
4467  compilation_info->osr_offset(), *compilation_info->code(),
4468  compilation_info->function_context_specializing());
4469  }
4470  CompilerTracer::TraceCompletedJob(isolate, compilation_info);
4471  if (IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
4472  CompilerTracer::TraceOptimizeOSRFinished(isolate, function,
4473  osr_offset);
4474  } else {
4475  function->UpdateOptimizedCode(isolate, *compilation_info->code());
4476  }
4477  }
4478  return;
4479  }
4480  }
4481 
4482  DCHECK_EQ(job->state(), CompilationJob::State::kFailed);
4483  CompilerTracer::TraceAbortedJob(isolate, compilation_info,
4484  job->prepare_in_ms(), job->execute_in_ms(),
4485  job->finalize_in_ms());
4486  if (V8_LIKELY(use_result)) {
4487  function->SetTieringInProgress(isolate, false,
4488  job->compilation_info()->osr_offset());
4489  if (!IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
4490  function->UpdateCode(isolate, shared->GetCode(isolate));
4491  }
4492  }
4493 }
4494 
4495 // static
4496 void Compiler::DisposeMaglevCompilationJob(maglev::MaglevCompilationJob* job,
4497  Isolate* isolate) {
4498 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
4499  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function = job->function();
4500  function->SetTieringInProgress(isolate, false, job->osr_offset());
4501 #endif // V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
4502 }
4503 
4504 // static
4505 void Compiler::FinalizeMaglevCompilationJob(maglev::MaglevCompilationJob* job,
4506  Isolate* isolate) {
4507 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
4508  VMState<COMPILER> state(isolate);
4509 
4510  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function = job->function();
4511  BytecodeOffset osr_offset = job->osr_offset();
4512 
4513  if (function->ActiveTierIsTurbofan(isolate) && !job->is_osr()) {
4514  function->SetTieringInProgress(isolate, false, osr_offset);
4515  CompilerTracer::TraceAbortedMaglevCompile(isolate, function,
4516  BailoutReason::kCancelled);
4517  return;
4518  }
4519  // Discard code compiled for a discarded native context without finalization.
4520  if (function->native_context()->global_object()->IsDetached(isolate)) {
4521  CompilerTracer::TraceAbortedMaglevCompile(
4522  isolate, function, BailoutReason::kDetachedNativeContext);
4523  return;
4524  }
4525 
4526  const CompilationJob::Status status = job->FinalizeJob(isolate);
4527 
4528  // TODO(v8:7700): Use the result and check if job succeed
4529  // when all the bytecodes are implemented.
4530  USE(status);
4531 
4532  if (status == CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED) {
4533  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(function->shared(), isolate);
4534  DCHECK(!shared->HasBreakInfo(isolate));
4535 
4536  // Note the finalized InstructionStream object has already been installed on
4537  // the function by MaglevCompilationJob::FinalizeJobImpl.
4538 
4539  DirectHandle<Code> code = job->code().ToHandleChecked();
4540  if (!job->is_osr()) {
4541  job->function()->UpdateOptimizedCode(isolate, *code);
4542  }
4543 
4544  DCHECK(code->is_maglevved());
4545  if (!V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL || IsOSR(osr_offset)) {
4546  OptimizedCodeCache::Insert(isolate, *function, osr_offset, *code,
4547  job->specialize_to_function_context());
4548  }
4549 
4550  RecordMaglevFunctionCompilation(isolate, function,
4551  Cast<AbstractCode>(code));
4552  job->RecordCompilationStats(isolate);
4553  if (v8_flags.profile_guided_optimization &&
4554  shared->cached_tiering_decision() <=
4555  CachedTieringDecision::kEarlySparkplug) {
4556  shared->set_cached_tiering_decision(CachedTieringDecision::kEarlyMaglev);
4557  }
4558  CompilerTracer::TraceFinishMaglevCompile(
4559  isolate, function, job->is_osr(), job->prepare_in_ms(),
4560  job->execute_in_ms(), job->finalize_in_ms());
4561  } else {
4562  CompilerTracer::TraceAbortedMaglevCompile(isolate, function,
4563  job->bailout_reason_);
4564  }
4565  function->SetTieringInProgress(isolate, false, osr_offset);
4566 #endif
4567 }
4568 
4569 // static
4570 void Compiler::PostInstantiation(Isolate* isolate,
4571  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
4572  IsCompiledScope* is_compiled_scope) {
4573  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(function->shared(), isolate);
4574 
4575  // If code is compiled to bytecode (i.e., isn't asm.js), then allocate a
4576  // feedback and check for optimized code.
4577  if (is_compiled_scope->is_compiled() && shared->HasBytecodeArray()) {
4578  // Don't reset budget if there is a closure feedback cell array already. We
4579  // are just creating a new closure that shares the same feedback cell.
4580  JSFunction::InitializeFeedbackCell(isolate, function, is_compiled_scope,
4581  false);
4582 
4583 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4584  if (function->has_feedback_vector()) {
4585  // Evict any deoptimized code on feedback vector. We need to do this after
4586  // creating the closure, since any heap allocations could trigger a GC and
4587  // deoptimized the code on the feedback vector. So check for any
4588  // deoptimized code just before installing it on the function.
4589  function->feedback_vector()->EvictOptimizedCodeMarkedForDeoptimization(
4590  isolate, *shared, "new function from shared function info");
4591  Tagged<Code> code = function->feedback_vector()->optimized_code(isolate);
4592  if (!code.is_null()) {
4593  // Caching of optimized code enabled and optimized code found.
4594  DCHECK(!code->marked_for_deoptimization());
4595  DCHECK(function->shared()->is_compiled());
4596  function->UpdateOptimizedCode(isolate, code);
4597  }
4598  }
4599 #endif // !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4600 
4601  if (v8_flags.always_turbofan && shared->allows_lazy_compilation() &&
4602  !shared->optimization_disabled(CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS) &&
4603  !function->HasAvailableOptimizedCode(isolate)) {
4604  CompilerTracer::TraceMarkForAlwaysOpt(isolate, function);
4605  JSFunction::EnsureFeedbackVector(isolate, function, is_compiled_scope);
4606  function->RequestOptimization(isolate, CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS,
4607  ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous);
4608  }
4609  }
4610 
4611  if (shared->is_toplevel() || shared->is_wrapped()) {
4612  // If it's a top-level script, report compilation to the debugger.
4613  DirectHandle<Script> script(Cast<Script>(shared->script()), isolate);
4614  isolate->debug()->OnAfterCompile(script);
4615  bool source_rundown_enabled;
4616  TRACE_EVENT_CATEGORY_GROUP_ENABLED(
4617  TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("devtools.v8-source-rundown"),
4618  &source_rundown_enabled);
4619  if (source_rundown_enabled) {
4620  script->TraceScriptRundown();
4621  }
4622  bool source_rundown_sources_enabled;
4623  TRACE_EVENT_CATEGORY_GROUP_ENABLED(
4624  TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("devtools.v8-source-rundown-sources"),
4625  &source_rundown_sources_enabled);
4626  if (source_rundown_sources_enabled) {
4627  script->TraceScriptRundownSources();
4628  }
4629  }
4630 }
